title: pecan lassies
directions: Cut butter and cheese into flour-like pie crust.
Form 24 balls.
Press into bottom and sides of miniature muffin pans.

title: aloha chicken
directions: Flatten the chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place the flour in a large resealable plastic bag.
Add the chicken and shake to coat.
In a skillet over medium heat, brown the chicken in oil for 3 to 5 minutes per side until the juices run clear. Remove the chicken from the skillet and keep warm.
Drain the pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup of juice.
In a small bowl combine the juice and cornstarch until smooth.
Add to the skillet.
Stir in the honey, teriyaki sauce and the pepper.
Boil for 30 seconds or until thickened.
Add the pineapple and chicken.
Heat through. Serve on a bed of rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: surprise pie
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add flour and nuts as soon as pan is cool enough to handle. Stir until all the margarine is absorbed in the flour.
Pat out to cover bottom of pan. Cook for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let this cool completely.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Mix all dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed ingredients.
Roll in sugar and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan with cold water to cover.
Add salt.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook, covered until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain and return to stove about 1 minute to dry.
Toss briefly with parsley and butter.
Serves 6.

title: plum sauce
directions: Boil plums for 8 minutes.
Drain off water.
Add vinegar to plums and bring to good boil. Mix cinnamon, cloves, allspice and sugar.
Add to plums and vinegar.
Boil for 45 minutes.
Pour in jars and seal while hot.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together and press in the bottom of greased and floured 13 x 9 pan.

title: una's famous fruit sandwiches
directions: Mix well. Spread on brown bread. Cut into triangles.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Cool.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice and soak cucumbers in the 2 gallons of water and lime overnight.
Wash several times to remove all lime.
Dissolve sugar, salt and alum in vinegar and add spices and washed cucumbers.
Let set about an hour.
Bring to a boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: ten minute fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler over boiling water in bottom of double boiler.
Add corn syrup, water, vanilla and stir.
Sift together confectioners sugar and dry milk. Gradually add to mixture in double boiler, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; add nuts and stir.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Mark into squares when mixture has set.
Cut when cool.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Toss together pork strips, cornstarch, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Heat oil until hot.
Add pork and garlic.
Stir-fry.
Add vegetables and mushrooms.
Cook 1 minute.
Mix hot water and bouillon. Add to pork.
Mix cornstarch, 1 teaspoon soy sauce and cold water.
Stir into pork.
Heat to boil. Stir and boil 1 minute.

title: raspberry punch
directions: After washing the raspberries, pour the vinegar over them and stir well.
Let stand 24 hours.
Then mash and strain through a sieve.
Add 3 cups sugar for each pint of juice.
Chill and serve one half juice to one half water, with mint leaves.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with a blender on low speed.
Chill and serve with whole strawberries or other fruits.

title: heart healthy spicy corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 15 minutes. Add green pepper to carrots and cook 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick. Pour over carrots.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix with mixer the cream cheese (softened), Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Refrigerate while cutting ham.
Mix in all other ingredients, except nuts, and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Shape into ball; roll in crushed walnuts.
Serve on crackers.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Combine cake ingredients, except nuts.
Beat for 2 minutes. Add nuts.
Stir with spoon to mix.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove from oven.
Puncture top with toothpick. Pour 2/3 Orange Glaze on top.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes. Remove from pan and top with remaining glaze.

title: quickie lorraine
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Spoon into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in 450° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: susan's old fashion apple stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and sorghum and mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients together. Add alternately with batter, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake in thin layers about 1/2-inch thick in either 9-inch pans or old fashion black griddle.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese drops
directions: Allow the butter and cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Cream together the softened butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Add the vanilla; mix well.
Gradually add the flour, beating in thoroughly.
Mix in the pecans.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Decorate the tops with chocolate morsels, one for each cookie.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 10 minutes.
(The cookies should be very lightly browned.) Makes 8 dozen small cookies.

title: cheesy baked eggs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish. Line bottom with bread slices.
Layer Mozzarella cheese, Cheddar cheese and bacon.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Beat until well blended.
Pour over bacon cheese mixture in baking dish.*
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.
Great for brunch.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix together butter and flour. Then add milk and mix. Roll out on a floured surface. Cut with a biscuit cutter. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl and add mayo to moisten.
Chill and serve.

title: snappy green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of the bacon fat until tender.
Add vinegar.
Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Pour over hot beans.
Crumble bacon atop. Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Broil steak 3 to 4-inches from heat for 5 minutes on each side or until browned.
Place steak in skillet.
Add undrained sauerkraut, tomato juice and onion slices.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Also can be done in the oven at 325° or 350°.
Put over mashed potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: meatless zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onions in oil until tender.
Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients, but add the eggs last. Place the mixture in a large casserole or two small ones (can be frozen well).
Use buttered breadcrumbs over top of casserole and little chunks of Velveeta cheese too, if liked.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: baker's dough
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together and knead until smooth.
Roll to a thickness of 1/8 to 1/4-inch and cut into desired shapes.

title: spaghetti pie(casserole)
directions: Cook the spaghetti; rinse with hot water and drain.
(Should have 3 cups.)
Stir the butter into the hog spaghetti.
Add the Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Pat this mixture into a 9 or 10-inch pie dish to form the "crust." Fill the "crust" with the cottage cheese.
Spread the heated spaghetti sauce over this.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cover top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until melted.
Serves 6.

title: quick chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare macaroni according to package. Add carrot, celery, onion and bouillon to macaroni during last 4 minutes; drain.
In small casserole, mix macaroni mixture, corn, 1/2 cup cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken on top. Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for an additional 10 minutes.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel eggplant. Cut into 1-inch chunks.
In skillet over medium heat, in 1/4 cup hot salad oil, cook eggplant and green onion until eggplant is very tender, 20 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently and adding more oil if needed.
Mash eggplant.
Mix flour, milk, baking powder, salt, oregano and eggs. Stir in eggplant.
Drop batter by scant 1/4 cupfuls in hot oil, turning once. Remove and drain on paper towels.

title: hamburger helper
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown hamburger or steak with mushrooms and onion; drain.
Lower heat and add ketchup, sour cream, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Let simmer for 15 minutes and add noodles.

title: chess cake
directions: Melt margarine, then combine cake mix, margarine and eggs. Put in cake pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and eggs together.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar that have been mixed together.
Place in a greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter, brown sugar and water on stove.
Boil 2 minutes and
pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemony apple bran salad
directions: Stir together yogurt, parsley, apples, celery and grapes. Cover and chill thoroughly.
At serving time, stir in All-Bran cereal.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix well with hands.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Grease hot griddle with margarine or butter (only necessary for first pancake).
Fry by putting 1/3 cup batter on griddle and tilt to spread batter.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, building up slight edges.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: turkey curry
directions: In stove top pan with cover, melt margarine over medium heat. Add onion, celery and apple; saute until tender but not browned. Sprinkle flour and spices over top and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Then stir in broth (use chicken if you don't have turkey) and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened. Add turkey and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Stir in raisins and serve immediately over hot rice.
Use curry condiments such as coconut, chopped peanuts and chutney.
Absolutely the best way to use remains from roast turkey.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Season and flour chicken.
Brown lightly in butter or margarine.
Place in a casserole dish, skin side up.
Sprinkle with slivered canned almonds, if desired (soak in water, if not canned).
Pour 1 can of mushroom, chicken or celery soup over chicken.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 375° for 1 hour or until soft.
Allow to cool.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato.
Scoop out the pulp.
Blend in milk, bacon, onion, chives, salt, pepper and 1 cup of cheese.
Spoon into potato shells.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Mix all ingredients (except tortillas) together in saute pan, cook thoroughly (like scrambled eggs) and roll into tortillas.

title: nanie's apple bread pudding
directions: Mix vanilla, sugars, eggs and milk in pan and heat on top of stove until just hot.
Add 1/4 stick of butter and continue heating until butter melts.
Arrange toasted bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour liquid over toasted bread. Place apple slices and raisins over bread.
Dot with pieces of butter. Sprinkle with a mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: roxie's honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Cut brown sugar and cinnamon in and swirl.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
While warm, mix confectioners sugar, vanilla and milk and drizzle on top.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Brown chicken in the cooking oil. Add garlic, salt, pepper, water, peppercorns, bay leaves, soy sauce, vinegar and sugar.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour or until chicken is tender, stirring frequently.
Remove bay leaves and peppercorns.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: turkey chili
directions: Cook turkey meat, onions, bell pepper and garlic until meat is light brown.
Add red pepper, chili powder and cumin, then add tomato sauce, water and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 45 minutes.
Stir in beans and sprinkle on chili mix to taste.
Simmer 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: ruth strickland's dip(for fresh fruit)
directions: Mix together equal parts.

title: millie's zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa.
Add to mixture of flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Stir.
Do not beat.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 400°
for 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Test at 20 minutes.

title: grape-nuts bread
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in milk for 15 minutes.
After soaking, combine with all other ingredients. Pour into loaf pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes in 350° oven.

title: italian gravy
directions: Lightly saute chopped garlic in hot oil.
Add can of Italian whole tomatoes.
Add tomato paste and stir in 2 (6 ounce) cans of water.
Add dash of salt and sugar.
Spread Italian seasoning in top.
Simmer 2 hours.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until thick and add sugar while beating constantly.
Add dates and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.

title: black-eyed pea salsa
directions: Place peas in colander; rinse under cold water.
Drain real good.
Combine tomatoes and next 7 ingredients in medium bowl. Stir in peas.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: daddy's barbecued chicken
directions: Melt margarine; combine dry ingredients and add to margarine. Stir until blended.
Remove from heat.
Combine remaining ingredients and gradually stir into butter mixture.
Return to heat and cook, stirring, until thick and smooth.
Makes enough for 2 chickens.
Brush with sauce as barbecue chicken.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: Cream softened butter. Gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in the pecans and cherries. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes or until tested done. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; drain well, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add flour, stir until smooth.
Add water gradually; cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring all this time.
Add the next five ingredients; stir well and bring to a boil.
Stir in bacon and remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine above ingredients well.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: trash
directions: Mix cereals, pretzels, and nuts in a large roasting pan. Melt margarine and blend remaining ingredients in melted margarine. Pour over cereal mixture and mix well. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: hearty pear breakfast muffins
directions: Peel and chop pears to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Combine pears, sugar, milk, oil, egg and raisins.
In a separate bowl, sift together remaining ingredients, except oats.
Stir in oats; add liquid mixture and stir just until blended.
Spray 16 muffin cups with cooking spray.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375°, about 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes about 16 muffins.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 1 gallon hot chocolate or use 1/3 cup mix to each cup.

title: squash relish
directions: Combine squash, onions and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours. Drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar, seeds and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add squash and onions.
Bring to a boil and boil for about 10 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Set aside. Combine vegetables; drain well.
Add vinegar mix and vegetables. Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: meatball and ravioli casserole
directions: Spray 12 X 9 inch sheet of foil with nonstick cooking spray. In large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into ungreased 11 X 7 inch glass baking dish.
Cover with foil, sprayed side down. Refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350. Bake covered for 40 minutes.
Uncover baking dish and sprinkle cheese evenly over the top.
Bake uncovered an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly and thoroughly heated.

title: judy's cucumber sandwiches
directions: Drain cucumbers well.
Mix with next 4 ingredients.
Drain again.
Spread, at last minute, and cut into finger sandwiches.

title: lemon pie
directions: Prepare dough for 2 pie crusts.
Grate lemons to make 2 teaspoons lemon rind.
Peel the lemons, removing all the white, then slice lemons as thin as possible.
Take all the seeds out. Add sugar.
Mix the lemons and sugar; let stand 20 minutes.
Beat eggs well.
Stir eggs into the lemon mixture.
Pour lemon mixture into pie shell.
Put top crust on.
Cut slits in top and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Very tangy and like lemon custard pie.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Mix well with all the ingredients.
Make into balls and refrigerate for 1 hour or more. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Can be frozen.
Make balls, put into bags and freeze.
Yields 70 balls.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Put on pizza pan.
Top with potatoes, sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over other ingredients.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until eggs are not running.
Makes 2 pizzas.

title: busy day meal in a jiffy
directions: Remove 1 pound frozen hamburger from freezer.
While you're waiting for this to thaw, crack 2 raw eggs into a medium size bowl.
Add bread crumbs.
Mix hamburger in well.
Feed to dog and go out to eat at your favorite restaurant.

title: deer jerky
directions: *You can add cayenne (red pepper) to make as hot as you want.

title: lasagna
directions: In large pan, brown beef.
Add spaghetti sauce; simmer 15 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well. Drop by heaping teaspoon full. Cook 8-10 minutes at 350. Cool 2 -3 minutes with pan on wire rack. Don't over cook.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil whole potatoes until tender; drain and slice potatoes. Put a layer of potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and butter.
When dish is filled, sprinkle top layer of potatoes with sugar, cinnamon, butter and orange peel. Add water; bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until brown and well candied.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumber and green onions in bowl.
Cover; let stand for 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumber mixture, mixing well.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chocolate cherry truffles
directions: Cut cake into slices. Open canned pie filling. Make instant pudding according to directions. Into large, deep bowl, layer cake, pudding and cherries. Keep layering until all is gone. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate, covered.

title: party cream puff appetizers
directions: Heat water, shortening and salt to boiling in a heavy saucepan. Quickly stir in flour and oats.
Stir vigorously over low heat about 2 minutes or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat; add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition until smooth and satiny.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake in hot oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Cut off tops and fill with crab meat, tuna or lobster salad.
Makes 40.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Boil all ingredients together for 20 minutes.
Pour into glass jars and seal.

title: ranger crispies
directions: Combine margarine, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour, soda and baking powder.
Add cereal. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 12 minutes.
Let cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Add rest of sugar, butter and salt to hot milk.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cool, then add egg.
Stir in softened yeast.
Stir flour into liquid ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Stir until flour and liquid are well mixed.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured board and knead it quickly until it is smooth and elastic.
Form dough into a smooth ball.
Place ball of dough in a greased bowl and turn it over once or twice to grease the surface.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in size, about 1 hour.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in butter.
Add stock and bring to boil.
Add Cream of Wheat.
Simmer, covered, 25 minutes.
Add spices.
Puree in blender or food processor.
Serve hot with Parmesan cheese and dash of sour cream.

title: hobo beans
directions: Cook and drain bacon and ground meat.
Saute onion and pepper in drippings and drain.
Combine all ingredients but vinegar in large baking dish or roaster and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add vinegar prior to serving and stir.
Serve hot.
Travels and reheats well.

title: spinach balls
directions: Boil spinach and drain.
Beat eggs and mix.
Make balls, 60 to 75 balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on cookie sheet (good appetizer).

title: any day meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper, garlic and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Mix lightly.
Shape into a loaf and place in shallow pan.
Combine remaining tomato sauce, water, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar, peanut butter and vanilla; roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate and wax together in top of double boiler.
Put toothpicks into candy, dip into chocolate and lay out on waxed paper to cool.

title: sunshine punch (slush)
directions: In saucepan, bring water and sugar to a boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil gently 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: minute fudge or frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan and cook 1 minute after it begins to boil. Stir until sugar and chocolate are melted but do not stir while candy is boiling.
Remove from heat and let set until hand can be held on bottom of pan. This is important. Beat until ready to pour.
Add vanilla and nuts during the last minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions in small amount of water until done; drain.
Blend in cheese and butter until fluffy.
Top with potato chips, enough to cover.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into loaf.
Put into pan.
Prepare sauce.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave.
Stir in mayo or salad dressing, green onions and parsley flakes.
Then add crabmeat, almonds, white wine, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Then microwave 4 to 6 minutes on Medium-high until hot.

title: southern belle meat loaf
directions: Saute pepper and celery.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into one-gallon churn and finish filling with milk.
Freeze.

title: shepherds pie
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain fat.
Add salt, salami, teriyaki marinade and onion.
Cook on low for 10 minutes.
Boil and mash potatoes.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Layer in baking pan: hamburg mixture and potatoes, then pour corn on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let sit for 1 hour before serving so it can settle (tastes better).

title: apple butter bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven.
Heat applesauce, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in saucepan.
Mix dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour melted butter into dry mixture and mix well.
Press 2/3 of mixture into bottom of pan.
Spread the heated applesauce over mixture.
Crumble remaining oat mixture on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a casserole, melt stick of butter in oven (400°).
Remove. Mix soups into butter; stir well.
Add 3/4 box Minute rice to mixture.
Stir well.
Add chicken and mix well.
Put layer (1/2-inch thick) of cornflake crumbs on top.
Cook at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl, except jello.
Fold together, then add dry jello and fold.
Put in dish and chill for several hours.

title: rancho bernardo ole' fish fillets
directions: Spray baking
dish
with Pam spray.
Lay fish pieces on bottom of	baking dish in single layer. Cover with the picante sauce. Oven
bake	or
microwave.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Layer vegetables, salt and ice and let stand for 3 hours. Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drain cucumbers.
Stir into syrup.
Stir from bottom until ready to boil.
Put into jars and seal.

title: caramelized banana pie
directions: Do this ahead of time:
Put unopened can of Eagle Brand milk in deep saucepan of boiling water.
(Be sure can is covered with water.)
Cover and boil gently for 2 hours.
Remove from water and cool before using.
May be stored in refrigerator for days.

title: four bean bake
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion in a large pan. Add beans. Stir in brown sugar, mustard and ketchup, to taste. Cook 1 hour.

title: layered shrimp spread
directions: Spread cream cheese on the bottom of a serving dish (quiche-size).
Brush with half of the cocktail sauce.
Layer shrimp on top of cream cheese and sprinkle with lemon juice. Layer with rest of the cocktail sauce, green pepper, onions and olives.
Top with Mozzarella.
Wrap tightly with aluminum foil and chill.
Serve with crackers or cocktail pumpernickel.

title: fish creole(microwave)
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry.
Arrange fish in 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan with thickest pieces to outside edges.
In 1-quart glass measure, stir together tomato sauce, mushrooms, green pepper, celery, water, minced onion and bouillon.
Pour evenly over fish.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, turning back corner to vent.
Microwave at High 8 to 10 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after 4 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving to blend flavors.

title: no-fail chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 2 minutes.
Take off heat and whip with mixer until stiff enough to spread.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, wash and cut into large pieces and add salt and water.
Boil until barely tender, drain.
Fry in hot fat until brown.
Place in baking pan.
Make a syrup with sugar.
Add water. Boil until it spins.
Pour over potatoes in pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned graham bread
directions: Mix together and put in bread tin.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine oranges, pineapple, coconut and sour cream.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve chilled.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: eggs tiffany
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix eggs, sour cream and butter; pour over layered ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Add to the above mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll in 1-inch balls. Roll balls in beaten egg whites and then finely chopped nuts.

title: deep fried eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 4 minutes.
Cool with cold water; peel carefully.
Roll eggs in flour; dip in beaten egg.
Roll in dry bread crumbs, seasoned with salt and pepper.

title: lively peanut butter ball
directions: Mix peanut butter, graham crackers, powdered sugar and margarine.
Roll into 1-inch balls, chill.
Melt chocolate and wax together until creamy.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Cool on wax paper.

title: german slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and bell pepper.
Combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and salt.
Bring to a boil 3 or 4 minutes. Cool for awhile, then add cabbage, onion and bell pepper.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Slice each baked potato in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center to form a shell.
Mash potatoes.
Combine with milk, butter, cream cheese, 1/2 Cheddar cheese and seasonings.
Beat until fluffy.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Mix apricots and coconut.
Add milk and blend well.
Shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Let stand until firm. Yield: 32 balls.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle wafer crumbs in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan.
In food processor, process cream cheese and next 7 ingredients. Process until smooth.
Add egg and process until just blended. Fold in chocolate mini morsels.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs. Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until cheesecake is set.
Let cool in pan or wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Remove sides of pan and transfer cheesecake to serving platter. Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: north carolina macaroni salad
directions: Mix macaroni with the onion, bell pepper and carrots.

title: chicken salad in peanut sauce
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tablespoons water.
Add peanut butter and stir until smooth, then add the remaining water, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, coriander, ginger and 4 slivered scallions; mix well.

title: mama berry's peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and peanut butter very slowly until it forms a soft ball in water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and salt.
Cool slightly and beat.
Pour in platter and cut into squares.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30-35 minutes or until tender. Drain well. Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight. Peel and grate potatoes. In a bowl, combine the eggs, 3/4 c. flour, bread crumbs, salt, nutmeg, and pepper. Add potatoes; mix with hands until well blended. Shape into 1-1/2 inch balls; roll in remaining flour.

title: frogmore broiled fish
directions: Lightly butter broiler pan and lay fillets on pan.
Baste fish with butter and sprinkle Old Bay on top.
Place oven rack on highest level and turn oven on broil.
Broil for 5 minutes or until top of fish turns brown.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Prepare 4 Jell-O's, each in 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring milk to boil; remove from stove.
Stir in sugar.
Add Knox gelatine.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Blend with mixer; do not overbeat.

title: lemon-honey chicken
directions: Season the chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in a baking dish.
Combine the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chicken, setting some aside.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Turn and baste while baking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut up chicken.
Put into casserole dish.
Put cream of chicken soup in and cover; bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes its own gravy for potatoes and rice.
Serves 4.

title: best ever chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender and remove meat from the bone. Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Skin, bone and pat dry chicken breasts.
Mix equal parts of Parmesan cheese and Progresso crumbs.
Dip each breast first in margarine, next in cheese/crumb mixture.
Roll up like a jellyroll and place on foil-lined, Pam-sprayed pan.

title: hot peppers and franks
directions: Wash peppers, remove seeds, slice both hot peppers and franks in a large kettle.
Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and garlic. Bring to a boil, add peppers and franks.
Return to boiling again and cook 10 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and process in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: chinese oven fried pork chops
directions: Spray a baking sheet with Pam cooking spray.
Beat together egg, soy sauce, ginger, garlic and water.
Dip chops in soy sauce mixture and then lightly coat with bread crumbs.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning chops after 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Heat a frying pan on the stove top, using medium-high setting, until a few drops of water sprinkled on the pan will dance around as they boil rather than stay in one place.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine in 4-quart saucepan sugar, water and syrup; cook until it is 230° (need a candy thermometer).
Over medium heat, add butter or margarine.
Cook until it is 302°.
Remove from heat; add soda and vanilla.
Beat until foaming reaches peak; pour into greased cookie sheet (prepared earlier) and spread thin.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Store in sealed coffee can.

title: quick and easy cobbler
directions: Place the fruit in a baking pan (9 x 9-inch or 9 x 13-inch) and sweeten as needed.
Measure flour and sugar in a small bowl; add the egg.
With a fork, work until it crumbles, then spoon over the fruit.
Bake in a 350° oven about 1 hour, or until brown.

title: ranch baked potatoes
directions: Put margarine, salt, pepper and half of Ranch dressing on bottom of casserole dish or flat pan.
Slice potatoes over this. Top potatoes with salt, pepper and Ranch dressing.
Cover and bake at 325° until done.

title: green punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, pineapple juice and water.
Mix well and freeze.
Two hours before serving, take out to thaw but not completely.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Punch should be slushy if desired.

title: coffee cake
directions: Add the sugar to the eggs and beat.
Add the salt, oil, flour and baking powder.
Use mixer for the entire batter.
Place 2/3 of the batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the pie filling over the batter, then the remainder of the dough.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: auntie's hot pot
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer onions, potatoes, then onions and potatoes.
Salt and pepper between each layer.
Place pork chops on top.
Add 3/4 cup water.
Sprinkle garlic and meat tenderizer on chops.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
In saucepan, melt butter; stir in frosting mix and rolled oats until crumbly.
Set aside.
In large bowl, blend sour cream, eggs and bananas until smooth.
Blend in cake mix; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.

title: figs and raspberry preserves
directions: Cook in large pot 24 to 30 minutes after they begin to boil, stirring constantly.
Wash your lids and jars in hot water.
Have them ready to pour preserves into.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, milk and lemon juice until smooth. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Let chill several hours.
Mix strawberries with strawberry gelatin and pour on top of filling.

title: hot taco casserole
directions: Crush Fritos on bottom of pan.
Spread with browned hamburger (any amount you want) or add taco seasoning to browned hamburger. Top with the 8 ounces of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.
Serve with chopped tomatoes, lettuce, sour cream and taco sauce.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients. Make sure all is wet. Drop by teaspoon into hot oil. Cook until brown.

title: lo-cal pineapple dessert
directions: Combine undrained pineapple and pudding mix.
Stir to dissolve pudding.
Stir in yogurt.
Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: linda's baked beans
directions: Brown together butter, ground beef and onion.
Mix brown sugar, salt, Worcestershire and mustard and add to meat mixture. Add cans of beans and top with Velveeta cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or put in crock-pot.
No picnic is complete without these beans.

title: brunch crescents
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Combine with horseradish. Unroll and separate rolls.
Spread with cheese mix; roll up and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake as directed on package.

title: crawfish spaghetti
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add cheese, soup, milk and crawfish.
Mix with cooked spaghetti in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: spinach pudding
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients finely in food processor.
Add eggs and seasonings; mix well.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups of bread crumbs. Spread butter onto a clean dish towel forming 9 to 10-inch square. Sprinkle with the remaining bread crumbs.
Drop the spinach mixture into the center and form a roll, 1 1/2-inches thick.
Wrap cloth loosely around the roll; tie ends and middle securely with string. Steam for 20 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake.
Thicken pineapple with cornstarch.
Watch closely while cooking.
When cool, add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Cut cake crosswise so you have 3 layers.
Spread cold pineapple between layers.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: butterscotch apple dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave:
In 1-quart glass measure, combine sweetened condensed milk, chips and salt.
Microwave on full power (High) 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes. Stir in vinegar and cinnamon.
Serve warm with apple wedges for dipping.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Can be made several weeks ahead.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator.

title: blender pie
directions: Blend in blender until all ingredients are well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: no bake cookies #2
directions: Prepare wax paper or foil on table.
In a pot, mix 2 cups sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes (no longer, no less), then cut fire off and add 1/2 cup peanut butter, oats, vanilla and dash of salt.
Sift and spoon out on wax paper or foil.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots on bias, 1/2-inch thick.
Cook until tender and drain.
Combine sugar, salt, ginger and orange juice in small saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots and coat evenly. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: cashew shrimp supreme
directions: Cut shrimp in half lengthwise.
Combine next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add shrimp and toss gently to coat.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Heat oil in a large skillet and add shrimp.
Cook, stirring constantly 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp and set aside. Drain off drippings, reserve 2 tablespoons in skillet.
Add onion, chopped red pepper and garlic to skillet.
Saute until tender. Add zucchini and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in shrimp, rice and cashews.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until well heated.
Spoon into serving dish.
Garnish with red pepper rings.

title: potato donuts
directions: Mix in	large
bowl.
Roll
small
portion at a time to 3/8-inch
thick.
Cut with donut cutter.
Deep fry until light brown.
Flip over and deep fry other side.	Cool and dust with 10x sugar.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix cooked sausage, cheese and Bisquick.
Stir in just enough milk to hold ingredients together.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot with butter and/or jelly.

title: spanish pickles (green tomatoes)
directions: Skin onions and tomatoes and slice thin.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 12 hours.
Wash in clear water.
Drain and add vinegar and sugar, heated to boiling with chopped peppers and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until transparent, about 1 hour.
Stir often.
Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: betty's raspberry bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in bowl; cut in butter and add milk.
Press mixture into buttered 10-inch pan.
Spread with raspberry jam almost to edge of pan.
Mix coconut, sugar, egg, butter and vanilla thoroughly and press into cake.
Bake in moderate oven until lightly browned.
Cut into squares while still warm to serve.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts. Roll into balls and bake 6 minutes at 375°.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, pudding and water with mixer at least 2 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until springs back to the touch.
While still hot, cut cake.
Cut piece in half.
Scoop ice cream inside.
Place top of cake back on.
Cover in syrup.
Garnish with whipped cream and cherry.

title: cold tongue(pressure cooked)
directions: Wash fresh beef tongue thoroughly.
Put on rack in pressure cooker.
Pour in water, salt, bay leaves, peppercorns, whole cloves and onion.
Cover and cook under pressure about 45 minutes. Follow time and instructions with your cooker.
Let cooker cool gradually; remove tongue.
Peel off skin and remove root ends. Enjoy!!!

title: cranberry orange ring
directions: Grate the rind from oranges, section and dice.
Dissolve salt and jello in boiling water.
Stir in sauce and orange rind.
Chill until slightly thickened, then fold in oranges and nuts.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes. Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle melted butter over all. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. This is great for brunch.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower, carrots, pepper and Cheddar cheese in order.
Mix salad dressing and sugar together; spread over vegetables.
Fry bacon crisp; cool and crumble over salad dressing.
Serves a bunch.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into loaf pan.
Bake at about 400° for 1 hour.

title: my favorite peanut butter cookie
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking soda together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add peanut butter chips.

title: corn relish(home canned)
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Place in a large stainless steel
or unchipped enamel sauce pot.
Cover with boiling water and boil 5 minutes.
Carefully drain and add remaining ingredients.
Prepare home canning jars and lids according to manufacturers instructions.

title: pecan coconut bars
directions: Mix well with pastry cutter and pat gently into 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Blend all ingredients together and roll out for pie.

title: juicy chicken balls
directions: Mix hamburger, water, salt and oatmeal; chill at least 30 minutes.
Form into balls and brown on all sides.
Add chicken soup; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: swedish rice ring
directions: Soften gelatin in water. Set aside.
In heavy 2 quart pan, bring rice, milk, sugar and salt to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat and cover.
Cook over low heat until rice is tender, about 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Cover.
Chill until partially set.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make sure it is not dry.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco salad(serves 15 well)
directions: Mix onion, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese together.
Add dressing.
Add chips, olives and green pepper.
Brown beef; drain. Add ketchup and dash of hot sauce.
Drain kidney beans, leaving just enough juice to simmer with hamburger for 10 minutes.
Cool and toss in salad.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet until the red is gone.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with chips or Hawaiian bread.

title: maid of honors(an english pastry)
directions: Make yellow cake batter.
Cream the butter and add salt and vanilla.
Gradually blend in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift the flour, measure and sift together with the baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to the cream batter and egg mixture.
Line muffin tins with pastry circles from the crust.
Into each pastry cup, put 1/2 teaspoon preserves (apricot, raspberry, cherries, etc.), then drop in a spoonful of cake batter.
Fill so that tin is 3/4 full as for cupcakes.
Bake in a 350° oven about 20 to 25 minutes until cake is done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
A wonderful treat for a bridal shower!

title: lecso (hungarian)
directions: Saute onions in oil (bacon fat is best) or margarine.
Add green peppers.
Fry some more.
Add tomatoes, paprika, tomatoes, water (more if required), parsley, cubes and sausage for 1 hour. Add eggs whole.
Also, good with sausage, fried pork chops or with fried bacon as main dish.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the pretzels with margarine and 3 tablespoons
sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread over this layer the following which should be creamed together: cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Combine jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Pour over other layers.
Refrigerate.

title: stacked taco salad
directions: In a medium skillet, brown the ground beef with the taco seasoning mix, stirring to break up the meat; drain and cool. In a large, clear glass bowl, layer half of the lettuce, then half of the cheese, beans, ground beef and tomatoes. Repeat the layers, then top with the crushed tortilla chips. Just before serving, drizzle with the dressing and toss to coat the ingredients well.

title: oatmeal caramel bites
directions: Melt caramels and milk in a pan; let cool.
Mix together oatmeal, brown sugar, butter,
soda
and salt.
Pat half of this mixture in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from
oven.
Sprinkle
chocolate
chips
and chopped nuts over base.
Pour caramel mixture over all and top with the rest of the oatmeal
mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate until serving time.

title: snowy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, mash and add everything except paprika and chives.
Beat until smooth.
Add chives, bake in lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie crust
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well. Sprinkle cold water, one tablespoon at a time, evenly over surface of mixture.
Stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: my mother's salmon patties
directions: Mix together ingredients. Flour your hands and form patties. Lightly flour patties and fry in grease until golden brown.
Easy and taste great.

title: aunt ella's cinnamon kuchen
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough; cover and keep warm and allow to raise until double in size.
Punch down and divide into 2 parts.
Pat down in a greased pie plate to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Let raise again until double.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until lightly browned.

title: perfection salad
directions: Mix together gelatin, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Place over medium heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin and sugar are dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining 3/4 cup water, vinegar or lemon juice. Chill until mixture is the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in cabbage, celery and green pepper.
Turn into a 6-cup mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens; serve with mayonnaise.
Yields six servings.

title: cream of carrot-potato soup
directions: Saute onion and butter in large kettle.
Add carrots, potatoes, broth and seasonings and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Finally, add milk and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve hot with parsley sprinkled over.

title: cranberry dream salad
directions: Process mayonnaise, sugar, cheese, cranberry sauce and nuts until chopped.
Fold in whipped cream and pineapple.
Freeze.

title: orange 7 punch
directions: Empty
orange juice into punch bowl; add water as directed for 1 can.
Add Seagrams.
Just before serving, add ice block, lemon lime soda and Amaretto.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 24 punch cups (4 ounces each).
You can double recipe.

title: micro sweet and sour turkey loaves
directions: In 1 3/4-quart casserole, combine sweet and sour sauce, 1/4 catsup, green pepper and peaches.
Set mixture aside.
In medium bowl, combine egg, bread crumbs, soy sauce, ginger, garlic powder and pepper.
Add turkey; mix well.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Arrange around edge of casserole in sauce.
Micro 8 to 10 minutes covered.

title: chicken with forty cloves of garlic
directions: In a large, deep skillet over medium-high heat, warm 1 tablespoon of the butter and the oil until hot.
Add the chicken; season with salt and pepper.
Brown it on all sides.
Distribute the garlic cloves around the chicken.
Cover and cook the chicken over medium-low heat for 30 to 35 minutes, or until juices run clear.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes; drain on paper towel.
Put in large mixing bowl with 1/2 cup margarine.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend.
Pour into buttered 3-quart baking dish.
Use remaining butter on bread crumbs and sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese danish
directions: Layer 1 crescent roll package on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. (Spray first with Pam.)
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, sugar and egg yolk.
Layer on top second package of crescent rolls.
Brush with egg whites and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Place in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight before serving.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook beef and onion; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread on greased pie plate.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients for casserole and put into large casserole dish.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix warm water and dry yeast; let set 10 minutes.
Add warm water, sugar, salt and flour.
Mix all together.
Let this set 3 days (covered) at room temperature, stirring the mixture down daily, then put in refrigerator.

title: basic biscuit dough
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Add milk and stir with fork until dough follows fork around bowl.
Then knead on lightly floured board 1/2 minute.
Bake in your desired shape at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Cook cubed potatoes in a small amount of water until tender; drain.
In a large saucepan, cook onion with seasonings in butter. Add soup, milk and water; heat.
Add chicken and corn.
Heat and stir occasionally. Good served over hot biscuits. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Place undrained pineapple in an 8-inch square dish.
Sprinkle pudding over pineapple and fold together.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Fold marshmallows into Dream Whip.
Mix marshmallow mixture and pineapple mixture together.
Decorate top with chopped nuts and cherry halves.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.
Recipe may be doubled and made in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: pineapple-ham style entree
directions: Thaw entree slices before using.
Melt margarine in baking dish or pan large enough to place slices individually, if possible.
Stick cloves around sides of slices or scatter over top.
Place in pan with melted margarine.
Combine cornstarch and pineapple juice and blend until smooth.
Add brown sugar and raisins. Mix well and pour over slices, covering well.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven until sauce thickens, about 20 minutes.
Baste several times during baking.
About 5 minutes before removing from oven, place pineapple rings on top of slices, baste with sauce and leave in oven long enough to heat pineapple.
Serve at once.

title: oatmeal cookies(low cholesterol)
directions: Heat oven
to
Beat
margarine
and sugars until light and
fluffy.
Beat	in
egg whites and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients;
add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop
by	rounded
tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake
to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie; 10 to 11 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on sheet; remove to rack. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: almost instant pierogis
directions: Drain and cool shells immediately under cold water.
Cool and drain cooked potatoes.
Add cheese to potatoes.
Mash; add salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter and add onions; cook until tender.
Spread 1/2 onions equally over 2 (9 x 13-inch) baking dishes.
Gently stuff each shell with heaping tablespoon of potato mixture.
Bring sides of shells together over filling.
Arrange in single layer on onions.
Spread remaining onions on top.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spiced fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale and crushed ice. Let stand for 3 hours.
Strain.
Add ginger ale and crushed ice. Makes about 15 cups.

title: bar-b-q slaw
directions: Mix cabbage with sugar, salt and peppers. Add ketchup and vinegar. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan or glass dish with Mazola or similar pan spray.
Spread uncooked rice evenly over bottom of pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice.
Mix canned soup, dry soup mix and water in a bowl.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated carrot salad(serves 12)
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water until crisp-tender. Drain and cool.
Combine carrots, onions and green pepper in a 2 1/2-quart bowl. Combine soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, oil and vinegar, sugar and salt in a small bowl.
Pour the marinade over the vegetables.
Stir gently to combine.
Cover. Refrigerate at least 24 hours to blend flavors.

title: cheezy mexican dip
directions: Mix together, refrigerate. Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: peach ice cream
directions: In large bowl, mix together eggs and sugar until smooth; puree peaches in blender or food processor and stir 5 cups of puree into egg mixture.
Stir in cream, half and half, vanilla and salt and mix well.
Pour mixture into freezer canister of ice cream maker and freeze according to manufacturers instructions.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Mix together cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple, undrained.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add yellow cake mix.
Do not stir!
Pour melted butter on top and add coconut and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble chicken into casserole dish, then mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup together and spread over chicken.
Pour stuffing mix over cream mixture, then pour chicken broth and butter over it. Bake for about 30 minutes until brown.

title: sweet minglers
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Stir in peanut butter and peanuts.
Mix real good.
Gently stir in cereal until well coated. Put powdered sugar in a 2-gallon plastic bag.
Add coated cereal and toss gently until well coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: take to work cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on
mix.
While
hot, pour milk over and chill overnight.
Mix sugar
and
Cool Whip and spread on cake.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and cocoa.
Add beaten whole eggs. Dissolve soda in milk and add to mixture.
Add flour last. Gradually add boiling water and flavoring very last.
Bake in moderate oven until done.
This batter will be thin.

title: red velvet cake(easy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cake mix last.
Add water to batter until mixture is thin enough to pour.
Use 2 layers or 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.

title: cocomia cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well with wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend sugar and butter.
Mix, forming a grainy paste.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture, coconut and Macadamia nuts.
Blend at low speed.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix milk and eggs.
Sift 1 cup flour with salt and baking powder.
Pour milk and egg mixture into flour and add only as much flour as needed to make a batter, not too thick to flow.
Pour batter into a good size funnel and let drip through funnel into deep fat.
Turn one time.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes on a baking dish, which has been sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Mix dressing, bacon, eggs, onions, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Add potatoes and mix lightly.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings; sometimes I double the recipe.

title: hot roast beef sandwich
directions: Brown onion in butter in skillet.
Add flour; stir until brown.
Gradually add milk.
Stir and cook until thick.
Add meat slices; cook 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Place between slices of bread, or on hot toast with gravy.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in graham cracker crusts.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, dill pickle dip and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add shrimp and fold in.
Serve with chips or a variety of vegetables.

title: texas brag cake
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle sugar on top.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit evenly.
Melt butter or margarine and pour over mixture until it is all covered. Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and mix. Add and mix milk and yeast mixture	until
all
flour is moistened.	Store in refrigerator.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Butter a deep baking dish, then starting at the bottom, put the ingredients into it in the following order: potatoes, ground beef, sliced onions, green pepper (if used), uncooked rice and tomatoes. Season each layer. Cover and bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: crawfish broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a 5-quart casserole, combine margarine, onions and bell pepper.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Add broccoli and microwave on High an additional 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; season to taste and microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring once.
Serve with salad and hot French bread.
Serves 8.

title: icebox cheese cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Form into a roll; wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight. Slice thinly and bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and sugar until smooth.
Form into small balls.
Refrigerate until cold.
Meanwhile, slowly melt chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Insert toothpick or fork tine in each ball, then dip 2/3 of ball in chocolate.
Let set on waxed paper.
Can be frozen for 6 months.

title: tasty wieners
directions: Dice the hot dogs; chop the onions, carrots, green and red peppers into small pieces. I use an electric skillet.
Brown diced hot dogs in olive oil.
Add onions, green and red peppers and saute for 10 minutes.
Be sure diced hot dogs don't burn.
Add quart of tomato juice, carrots and remaining herbs.
Cook on low to medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add pepper as desired. (You could include celery and garlic if so desired.)
Stir occasionally throughout mixing process. Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: fudgy wudgy chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a 2-quart glass bowl, cook chocolate with butter in a microwave oven on High 1-2 minutes, or until melted and smooth when stirred. Mix in flour until well blended. Add vanilla and sweetened condensed milk and mix well. Stir in pecans. Drop dough by Tbsp. 2 inches apart onto 2 greased foil-lines cookie sheets. Bake 9-10 minutes. Let cookies cool on baking sheets. Carefully remove from foil.

title: goop and scoop dip
directions: Mix the first six ingredients all together.
Refrigerate. Before serving, scoop out the inside of the bread loaf.
Spoon the dip mixture into the bread shell.
For dipping, you may arrange bite sized pieces of the scooped-out bread around the base of the shell.
If you prefer, you may arrange a variety of raw vegetables instead.
(Make croutons or use the bread in another recipe.)

title: creamy rich corn chowder
directions: Cook diced bacon in a kettle until crisp.
Remove and reserve.
In the fat, saute onion until tender.
Add potatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are barely tender.
Add the corn, salt and pepper and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Stir in cream and heat to boiling.
Sprinkle top with cooked bacon.

title: party rye bread pizzas
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Melt cheese in butter.
Combine sausage and cheese.
Add all other ingredients.
Spread on party rye bread.
Freeze on cookie sheets, then put in plastic bags and keep in freezer until ready to serve.
Cook at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Combine butter and 1/3 cup of water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir into dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts; mix well.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square dish.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Cut into squares.

title: pam's shrimp etouffee
directions: Mix together and simmer until vegetables are tender; add shrimp. Cook just until shrimp are done; about 10 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: brown rice, vegetables and fruit *(low-fat, practically nonfat)
directions: Spray nonstick pan with Pam.
Saute carrots for about 15 minutes.
Add onions and apples; cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in rice, salt and raisins.
Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes very well. Reheat, covered, in microwave.

title: mock pink champagne
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil in large saucepan.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Let stand to cool.
Add juice concentrates.
Chill in refrigerator.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and grenadine syrup.
Serve at once.

title: golden squash bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine eggs, cottage cheese, flour and bouillon.
Add squash; mix well.
Turn into greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apricot dessert
directions: Combine and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not bake.

title: one bowl cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and blend well with a wooden spoon.
Put into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
When cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut slices right from pan.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together with spoon until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 325°
for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Put in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put cut up chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder to suit taste.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over next, then grated cheese.
Put little oleo over and cook until cheese is melted.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn christmas tree
directions: Melt caramels, with water, in saucepan over low heat.
Toss popcorn with salt in large shallow roasting pan.
Pour caramel mixture over popped corn; toss until well coated.
With hands slightly wet with cold water, form into 36 balls.
Use 11 balls as circular base; stack remaining balls to form Christmas tree. Decorate with gumdrops, if desired.

title: jerk wings with ranch dipping sauce
directions: For Ranch Dipping Sauce, combine mayonnaise, yogurt, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder, 1/4 teaspoon black pepper and onion powder in small bowl.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple (reserve pineapple).
Add juice to Jell-O and marshmallows; heat over medium heat until marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese.
Stir until cream cheese is dissolved.
Add pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: mexico mission cookies
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together until well mixed.
Add remaining ingredients.
When all are mixed together, roll into tiny balls.
Press with a fork on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco and milk on medium speed until well blended.
Add brown sugar and sugar gradually.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
In another bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix together the two mixtures with wooden spoon.
Stir in white chocolate and nuts.
Drop 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for about 8 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: french apple pie
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar and mix well.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in buttered 8-inch pie plate for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Put in casserole dish. Melt cream of mushroom soup, cheese and butter in saucepan until well blended.
Pour sauce over broccoli and top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Enjoy!

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Combine all dry ingredients. Combine egg, milk, buttermilk and vanilla and add to dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Makes a soft dough.
Roll thin, cut and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: nestle toll house pan cookies
directions: Cream sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips last.
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 35 squares.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry; bake and cool.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Gradually stir in water, blending until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until filling comes to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir small amount of filling into beaten egg yolks, mixing thoroughly.
Cook 1 minute; remove from heat and stir in butter, lemon juice, vinegar and lemon peel.
Cool.
Add meringue.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: sad cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 9x13 pan for 30-40 minutes at 350°.
When cool cut into squares.

title: peanut candy
directions: Cook syrup, water, sugar and peanuts until peanuts start popping.
Add soda; stir.
Take up at once.
Pour on greased platter.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Flatten chicken breasts with meat mallet.
Place ham and cheese on chicken.
Roll and secure with toothpick.
Dip chicken in eggs; roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in skillet in butter.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Crush corn chips.
Add half of the can of tomato sauce and the taco seasoning to the beef.
Line a two-quart casserole dish with two cups of corn chips and spoon meat on top.
Combine remaining tomato sauce with beans and pour over meat.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese and add remaining corn chips.
Bake for five more minutes.

title: chinese chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, soy sauce and seasonings in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: wine cake
directions: Beat 5 minutes.
Pour into greased angel food cake tin and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
(Glaze with any favorite recipe.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan, mix with soups and water. Spread rice on bottom of ungreased glass casserole, pour a little more than half of soup mixture into casserole over rice.
Place chicken on top of rice, pour remaining soup mixture on top of chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in 275° oven for 3 hours.
Chicken will brown as it bakes.

title: birthday supper casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package, then drain.
Mix all ingredients together except for bread crumbs and butter or margarine and place in a buttered casserole.
Make buttered bread crumbs and sprinkle over the top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli and carrots.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch or 8 x 14-inch pan.
Dump in cherry pie filling, then pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Next, add coconut, then margarine, cut up.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mama bell's chocolate pudding cake
directions: Sift flour once, then again with baking powder and salt added. Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk. Add vanilla.
Pour into greased baking dish or pan.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup chips; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in same bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk, egg and vanilla, stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups chips and nuts.
Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon over low heat until crisp. Remove from pan. Add onion and celery to fat; cook until tender.
In saucepan, add onion, celery, corn, evaporated milk, water and seasoning.
Add 2 large diced, partly cooked potatoes.
Heat through. Before serving, add crisp bacon.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat cream in pan, gradually adding marshmallows.
When marshmallows are melted, pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: crabmeat soup
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Add all ingredients except crabmeat and simmer until macaroni shells are tender.
Allow soup to "rest" in pan for 20 minutes or so.
Then season to please your taste with salt, pepper, dill and any herb (i.e., oregano, basil, etc.).
Add crabmeat and heat just before serving.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend sugar and flour.
Add melted butter to sugar mixture. Beat eggs and add to the mixture. Add syrup and pecans.
Bake in uncooked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fun apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon. Toss apples in sugar mixture.
Put apples into 8 x 8-inch pan. Add any excess sugar mixture.
Pour dry cake mix over apples and pack tightly.
Cut 1 stick margarine into pieces and place over top of dry mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center and add all remaining ingredients.
Stir until just mixed.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion, drain and salt, pepper. Combine meat and remaining ingredients in crock pot.
Grate cheese on top.
Heat 2 hours until or until cheese is melted.

title: easy bleu cheese dressing(yields 1 cup)
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt 2 sticks margarine, then mix peanut butter, sugar and vanilla wafers together with margarine.
Chill, then roll into 1-inch balls.
In a double boiler, melt paraffin (1/4 to 1/2 cake) with chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate, using a spoon. Drop onto waxed paper.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in pie crust 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Shape into oblong sticks and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 or 8 minutes.
Do not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Use 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir into apples.
Arrange in pie shell.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until apples are tender.
Remove foil.
Combine sour cream and brown sugar.
Pour evenly over apples.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Bake for 2 to 3 minutes more or just until sour cream topping is set.

title: mexicali bean bake
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil until tender.
Blend in flour; stir in beans, tomatoes, chilies and pepper sauce.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat. In bowl, combine cornmeal, salt and soda.
Stir together egg, milk and the 1/4 cup oil.
Add to dry ingredients along with corn.
Mix well (mixture will be thin).
Pour about 2/3 of the cornmeal mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole or a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese; spoon bean mixture over all.
Spoon remaining cornmeal mixture around edge.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cornbread is done.
Serves 6.

title: sourdough start(serving size:  1)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let stand in a warm place overnight or up to 48 hours.
The longer the Start stands, the stronger the fermenting will be.
After fermenting the Start, it is ready to store in the refrigerator.
"Feed" the Start once or twice a week.

title: hearty ham supper
directions: Make a sauce of oleo, flour, milk and cheese.
Combine other ingredients in baking dish.
Pour sauce over this.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Cut fine first 6 ingredients and toss together.
Mix together next 6 ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: arizona grapefruit salad
directions: Cut grapefruit from top to bottom. Cut into segments with juice to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add grapefruit segments and juice. Pour into cleaned grapefruit and refrigerate.
Mix flour, sugar, lemon and pineapple juice, egg yolk and cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Fold in 1/2 cup whipped cream.
Spoon on top of grapefruit to serve.

title: heavenly potatoes
directions: Fold together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand awhile before serving.

title: raisin-butter tarts
directions: Cream oleo; add brown sugar.
Beat together, then add egg, syrup and vanilla.
Then add raisins, nuts and salt.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 tarts.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and remove bones and skin.
Flake salmon, add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Set this dish into a pan of water.
Bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Place mushrooms on top of this.
Place onions on top of mushrooms, spread cheese on top of onions.
Beat eggs and milk together, add Bisquick, salt and pepper and pour over layers of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown. Cut in squares and serve.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Mix everything else together and stir in drained, cooked spinach.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Turn
on
oven
to
Place
margarine in a mixing bowl. Let
soften
at
room temperature or heat one minute in microwave. Add oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and baking powder. Using your hands, mix it, mash it, squish it, pound it, until all
the ingredients
are mixed together.
Roll into ping-pong sized balls and place on a cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10
minutes at 350°.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: breast of chicken on rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend soup and milk.
Reserve half of mixture.
Stir together remaining soup mixture with rice, mushrooms with liquid and half of the onion soup mix.
Pour into an ungreased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts on rice mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, or until done. Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: lasagna
directions: Simmer together for 2 hours.

title: hash browns
directions: Defrost potatoes enough to separate into pieces.
Combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 cups crushed corn flakes with 1/4 cup melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: *Note:
I do not use water and I do not drain the beans.

title: pig lickin good cake
directions: Put your oil and eggs in the cake mix.
After you mix for about 4 minutes, add your oranges.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oats in buttermilk until soft.
Cream brown sugar, shortening and egg together.
Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder together.
Combine all together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
You may bake part and keep remainder in refrigerator.

title: custard pie (1)
directions: Set oven for hot (425°).
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry. Beat egg slightly, stir in sugar and salt.
Add milk gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and melted margarine. Press into oblong cake pan. Combine eggs, vanilla, powdered sugar and 1/4 pound butter. Beat for 2 minutes and spread over crumbs in pan. Press sliced bananas and pineapple into filling. Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with chopped nuts and cherries. Chill.

title: pork chops florentine
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart oblong baking dish.
Brown chops in oil, seasoned with pepper.
Cook spinach according to directions, but reduce cooking time to 5 minutes.
Drain spinach.
Fold in soup and pour in baking dish.
