Arrange chops on top of spinach mixture. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cornbread tamale pie
directions: Brown meat with onion. Drain off grease.
Add tomato soup, water, pepper, salt, chili powder, corn and green pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Prepare cornbread batter as directed on box.
Pour cornbread batter on top. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Mix sugar and syrup in saucepan and bring to boil. Add butter and pour hot mixture over eggs. Add pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell that has been sprinkled with a mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon flour. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: bananas flambe
directions: In a chafing dish or saucepan, melt butter and sugar with cinnamon; cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, about 3 minutes.
Into a chafing dish, cut bananas diagonally into 1/2-inch slices.
Heat through, carefully turning slices to coat.

title: zucchini monterey
directions: Brown the ground beef with the onion, then add the zucchini and cook until tender, then add rice, green chilies, salt, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes, cheese and sour cream.
Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crushed corn chips. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars(makes 48)
directions: On low speed, combine cake mix, 2 eggs, butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin spice until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan, then bring to a soft boil.
Add vanilla.
Pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: no-fault pie crust
directions: Mix first three ingredients well; set aside.
Mix next three ingredients and combine with the first three.
Roll out as for crust.
Makes enough for 2 single crusts or a double crust pie.

title: grandma m.'s frozen dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese and powdered (confectioners) sugar.
Add thawed strawberries, pineapple, banana, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix all together; freeze overnight.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased
9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and water.
Stir well over medium heat.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over the chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted butter over stuffing. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: millie's hot potato chip chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the chicken soup and potato chips.
Place in a fairly deep baking casserole.
Spread the can of chicken soup over top and cover with the crushed potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased iron skillet. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions until transparent. Remove from heat and stir in flour, salt, pepper and curry powder. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir this liquid into flour mixture and blend in evaporated milk until it starts to thicken.
Arrange cooked broccoli spears and chicken on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour milk and mushroom mixture over top and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Crumble brownies; place in bottom of dish. Mix chocolate pudding according to directions and spread over brownies.
Spread entire container of Cool Whip over pudding. Chill until ready to serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook together zucchini and onion in small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Mix together carrot, sour cream and soup with zucchini mixture.
Mix together butter, cornbread stuffing.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place half of stuffing mixture in bottom, then add vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kathy's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 10 minutes. This makes a huge amount of cookies.

title: low-fat salmon patties
directions: Mix everything together, except margarine, and make into patties.
Saute until brown in margarine in a Teflon skillet.

title: corn casserole(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Brown sausage and onion, then drain. Beat eggs until fluffy. Mix all ingredients together, except cheese. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Remove; add cheese and bake for about 10 minutes more.

title: skillet chicken and broccoli
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook and stir until brown.
Stir in soup, broccoli and water; bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir; sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: side dish salad
directions: Three or 4 hours before serving, slice pepper, cucumbers and onions.
Place vegetables in bowl; sprinkle with salt, then refrigerate.
Mix vinegar with sour cream or yogurt.
Just before serving, drain vegetables.
Add sour cream or yogurt.
Mix well. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix above ingredients together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9 inch).
Bake at 350 degrees until done, about 35 minutes.

title: thin crust pizza(no oil)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine 2 1/2 cups of flour and salt.
Stir in yeast mixture; knead 10 minutes, working in 1/2 cup more flour so it's still soft, but not sticky.
Put in bowl and cover.
Rise 45 to 60 minutes.
Punch down; rest 10 minutes before shaping.
Bake at 475° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan. Sprinkle coconut next.
Prepare cake mix as directed on the box. Pour cake mixture over coconut and pecans.
Melt butter and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour this over chocolate mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix dry ingredients and make a well in the center.
Aside, combine strawberries, 4 eggs well beaten and applesauce.
Pour liquid mixture into well and mix slowly until well blended.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: old-fashioned tea cookies
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder; add to the sugar mixture, then add milk and vanilla.
Now add more flour if needed.
Cut into any shape. Bake in oven about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding cake(texas sheet)
directions: Mix in bowl sugar and flour. Melt in pan and bring to a boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Combine the mixture and mix well. Add buttermilk and 2 slightly beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in preheated oven at 375°
in a 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
While cake is baking, begin making icing.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain grease.
Add chili powder, enchilada sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Line 3-quart casserole dish with a layer of tortillas, then a layer of meat mixture and layer up.
Mix soup, milk and green chilies.
Pour soup mixture over the top.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 6

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place in fridge to chill awhile. Blend together mayonnaise, salt and marjoram.
Add to chicken mixture, tossing to coat all ingredients.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add egg.
Stir in syrup.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Drop by 1-inch balls in 1/4 cup sugar.
Coat with sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Clean and steam broccoli.
Fry in butter cleaned and sliced carrots, mushrooms and chopped onions.
Then mix together all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: curried chicken
directions: Brown chicken in first 3 ingredients.
In skillet, add all the remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until done.
Serve over rice.
(Use curry to taste.)

title: apple cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add lemon juice to chopped apples.
Add apples, walnuts and raisins to mixture.
Combine eggs and oil mixing well.
Stir egg/oil mixture into batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: chicken and vegetables supreme
directions: Melt oil and butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Swirl chicken in melted fat.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 400°.
Drain off oil.
Place cheese on top of chicken, then layer vegetables and mushrooms on top. Mix together soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and thyme.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 400° or until chicken is tender.
Can be made day ahead and refrigerated.

title: skillet sausage supper
directions: Fry sausage and set aside to drain.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1/4 cup to sprinkle over batter.
To remaining crumbs, add the baking powder, soda and spices; mix thoroughly.
Add milk and eggs; mix well.
Pour into wax paper lined 8-inch pan. Sprinkle the reserved crumbs on top.
Chopped nuts and cinnamon may also be sprinkled over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Combine mushrooms, green pepper and margarine; cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium-high heat until thick and bubbly.
Add chicken bouillon, milk and water; keep stirring.
When thick and creamy, add chicken until warm.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugars, butter, cocoa and milk until it forms soft ball. Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and cut into squares.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter and add sugar, milk and cocoa.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add oatmeal.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir together and drop by tablespoons on foil or wax paper.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour; measure.
Add salt and spices.
Sift again.
Add chopped nuts and raisins.
Add shortening.
Add sugar gradually and continue to beat until light. Stir the soda into pumpkin.
Add beaten egg.
Combine with the creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Put 2 or 3 inches apart on a greased baking pan.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix margarine and cheese first, then add other ingredients. Add 2 cups Rice Krispies; mix well. Make balls and place on pans. Flatten with fork. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Makes about 75.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla. Add flour and nuts. Chill dough for 1 hour.

Mold 1 tablespoon around on unwrapped Kiss. Bake 12 minutes at 375° on an ungreased cookie sheet. Cool slightly and while still warm; roll in confectioners sugar. After cooling, roll again. Store in tight container.

title: greek bean soup(fasolatha)
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Rinse beans and cover generously with water.
Cover pot; allow to simmer slowly for about 2 hours.
Add hot water while cooking to keep beans covered.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Blend sugar, cream cheese and salt.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir in fruits and nuts and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving time and cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with fresh strawberries if desired.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: mahogany pound cake
directions: Sift flour and cocoa together; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, combine butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine sour cream and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until fluffy; fold into batter.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
When cool, remove from pan and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: old fashion chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Wesson oil.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and soda together.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat until mixed well (2 minutes).
Bake into layers (makes about 6 layers) for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine macaroni, carrots, green pepper and onion.
In separate bowl, whisk mayo, milk, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper until smooth. Pour over macaroni and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until crispy done.
Drain and place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: hamburger paprikash with noodles and broccoli
directions: Brown beef.
Stir in garlic and frozen onion and pepper.
Cook until thawed.
Stir in paprika and thyme.
Add broth, noodles (uncooked) and broccoli; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring twice, until noodles are tender.

title: peppermint fudge cake
directions: Crush 8 mints.
Set aside remaining mints for garnish.
Spread 1 cup of whipped topping on 1 cake layer.
Sprinkle with crushed mints.
Top with second cake layer.
Frost entire cake with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with remaining mints before serving. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Store leftover in refrigerator.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash sauerkraut.
Mix sugar and vinegar; heat until sugar melts.
Pour sugar and vinegar mixture over all mixed ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
This salad keeps well for 1 to 2 weeks. (Packed sauerkraut can be found in the meat counter.)

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand. Beat eggs, oil and vanilla until smooth. Mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; stir into egg mixture, alternating with apple mixture. Blend in raisins and walnuts. Pour into buttered and floured 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Let stand in pan until cool, then turn out on wire rack. Frost with Lemon Butter Frosting and decorate with whole walnut meats.

title: no bake cheese cake(low carb)
directions: In glass cup, sprinkle gelatine over water. Let stand for 2 minutes. Microwave on High until hot. Stir until dissolved. Add cream cheese cubes. Stir until dissolved. Blend with mixer. Add sugar substitute, vanilla and pudding mix. Pour into 12 paper lined muffin tins. Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Wash and slice squash; cook until done, about 10 minutes. Drain well.
Arrange in a buttered 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Melt butter; add cheese, sour cream, salt, paprika and onion.
Pour over squash.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup bread crumbs and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherokee squash casserole
directions: Cook together in boiling salted water until tender the squash, onion and bacon grease.
Drain and mash well.
Add while hot the grated cheese and butter or margarine.
Add cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter until soft; blend in sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Roll dough into small balls and place on a well greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes.
Roll puffs in powdered sugar while hot and again when cooled.
Yield 2 dozen puffs.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix crumbs, salt, paprika and pepper. Dip each piece of chicken in buttermilk, then coat with crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken pieces in single layers in a shallow pan.
Cover pans tightly with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil.
Increase oven temperature to 450°.
Brush chicken pieces with butter and put in oven for 15 minutes to brown.

title: pan american pork chops
directions: Crush oregano, parsley, garlic and 1 teaspoon salt together until well blended.
Add lemon juice and 1 tablespoon oil.
Mix well.

title: cheese pimento spread
directions: Stir well beaten
eggs,
sugar (more or less to taste), salt and vinegar.
Stir	and
cook
while
adding milk.	Grind cheese and pimento; add to mixture whole hot, so cheese melts.

title: no guilt brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Over very low heat, melt chocolate.
Cool slightly in food processor.
Puree all ingredients, except chocolate and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add melted chocolate and blend well.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, butter and 7-Up; bring to boil.
Pour into a baking dish.
Pat biscuits flat and fill with apple slices; fold in half.
Place in sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: red beans and rice(new orleans style)
directions: Rinse beans well and drain.
Place beans in large pot, cover with water.
Add ham bone, bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes.
Add sausage and cook covered over low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add garlic, onion, celery, peppers, scallions and bay leaf.

title: goulash with shells
directions: Boil shell macaroni as directed.
Brown hamburger until done. Pour in Ragu sauce; simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix macaroni and sauce.
Serve.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut first 3 ingredients together with knives or crust cutter. Mix remaining and add to flour mixture.

title: lajuana's viennese coffee
directions: Combine ingredients and store in a jar.
To make 1 cup coffee, mix 4 teaspoons of mix with 8 ounces boiling water.
Makes around twenty cups.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken, cut into pieces and place in a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Heat together soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Crumble corn bread and mix crumbs with 1 cup broth, sage and onion.
Place on top of soup mixture.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: char siu ribs
directions: Boil ribs in water until 1/2 cooked (about 20 minutes). Mix all
of
the remaining ingredients together in bowl; pour over hot,
drained
ribs.
Let it soak for 3 hours.
Charcoal over grill until slightly browned.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Put grated apples in a pie shell.
Mix sugar, egg and margarine.
Pour this mixture over apples.
Cook on 375° until golden brown.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: With a cheese slicer, cut cream cheese across top.
Place slice of cream cheese over slice of ham.
Cut into strips.
Start at straight end and roll up. Secure with fancy toothpick.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: eileen munson potatoes(delicious)
directions: Cook potatoes; peel warm and grate.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Mix together; sprinkle cheese on top.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: good coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Make 2 layers.
Let cool. Put on crushed pineapple, then whipped topping, then coconut.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Place on stove and cook until light brown color.
Take off stove and add milk.
Put back on stove and cook until mixture drops heavy from spoon.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prick pie shell bottom and sides with a fork.
If using metal pie pan, bake shell in preheated 450° oven until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
If using pie plate, bake at 425°.
Reduce oven temperature to 375° for metal pan or 350° for pie plate.

title: hamburger special
directions: Mix ground beef and eggs in a large bowl.
Add salt and pepper. Roll or crush crackers until they are really fine.
Add to meat mixture.
Make into average size patties.
Brown in skillet.
Place in cooking dish and pour cream of mushroom soup with small amount of water over.
Place in oven and cook for about 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Melt the butter in skillet and add chopped onion.
Cook over low heat.
When onion becomes transparent, then add your broccoli and cook just until pieces are all separated.

title: simple quiche
directions: Crumble bacon into pie shell, cover with grated cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and seasonings.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 25 minutes.

title: italian sausage casserole
directions: Pour vermouth or water in a skillet and crumble in the sausage, squeezed out of their casings.
Cook until lightly browned, breaking up lumps with a fork.
Pour off fat and add tomatoes.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes until sauce is no longer watery.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.

title: broccoli - cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces. Add onion, bacon and cheese. Add dressing mix to cover vegetables. Chill; refrigerate leftovers.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and wash cucumbers; slice very thin.
Place in bowl. Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 1 hour or longer.
Squeeze cucumbers dry.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the cucumbers.
Mix well and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salsa casserole
directions: First you brown the hamburger.
Drain it.
Mix salsa and salad dressing.
Stir in corn, then chili powder.
Take a glass baking dish and take half of your mixture; put it in the bottom of your pan, then half the chips and cheese.
Repeat, leaving cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven 20 minutes.

title: black russian cake
directions: Mix liquid ingredients.
Add yellow cake mix and pudding.
Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tomato pie(men love this!)
directions: Bake pie shell 10 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Layer tomatoes in shell, sprinkling each layer with salt, pepper, basil and garlic powder.
Combine mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread over tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until browned and bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add vegetables, dressing and Salad Supreme.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: peanut butter breakfast bar
directions: Combine eggs, peanut butter and honey; add dry milk and mix until well blended.
Add cereal and mix until evenly coated. Spread in greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Cut into bars.
Makes 6 bars.

title: honey-glazed ham
directions: Score ham.
Place, fat side up, on rack in shallow baking pan. Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 2 hours and 30 minutes. Mix honey, brown sugar and orange juice concentrate.
Bake ham for 30 minutes longer, basting frequently with honey mixture.
Yields 12 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses. Beat slightly.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Roll into balls. Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.
Roll in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: ham salad sandwiches
directions: Grind bologna and pickles.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Some pickles are juicier than others, therefore, you may need more or less mayonnaise.
Hard-boiled egg may be added, also.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press in bottom of a 13 x 9 pan.
Combine first layer, 2 sticks margarine, 2 c. powdered sugar and 2 eggs and mix at high speed at least 10 minutes, spread over crust.
Slice bananas and spread over first layer, drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Spread cool whip over pineapple.
Top with drizzled chocolate, nuts and halved cherries.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine corn and eggs.
Add flour which has been sifted with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat griddle or skillet over medium hot heat with Pam or a little oleo.
If batter seems too thick, add a little milk.

title: tomato ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in stewed tomatoes (broken up well with spoon).
Add Tabasco sauce.
Pour into shallow pans (two to three 9 x 12-inch pans).
Chill until firm.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch (or a little smaller) pan with chilies after taking out the seeds.
Put cheese on top.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over cheese and chilies.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Pour over top the tomato sauce and bake 5 minutes more.

title: tomato vegetable soup(diabetic)
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add macaroni and cook until macaroni is done.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Dissolve sugar in syrup over medium heat.
Cook until clear. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and blend.
Pour in cornflakes; cover them well with mixture.
Drop on wax paper. Cool and eat.

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash figs and add soda.
Cover with hot water; let stand 5 minutes, then rinse well.
Add sugar and start cooking.
Add juice of lemon and cut peeling into small slices.
Cook 30 minutes first day and then set aside.
Cook 30 minutes second day and then set aside.
Cook 30 minutes third day or until desired thickness and syrup will be clear.
Seal when hot in hot jars, using paraffin to cover preserves before applying lid.

title: texas chocolate pie
directions: Combine 2 cups of milk, sugar, cocoa and margarine in large saucepan. Bring just to a boil over medium heat.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into cup.
Add water to make 2 cups. Boil liquid and dissolve Jell-O.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour all ingredients into pie filling.
Mix well and refrigerate until Jell-O sets.
(Use Tupperware container.)
Cover congealed salad with topping and return to refrigerator.

title: quick and easy cheese ball
directions: Cheese must be at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Form into ball and cover with chopped parsley or nuts.
Chill until firm.
Also good using 1 jar olive pimento and 1 jar pimento.
Decorate with green olives.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and condensed milk, then add Cool Whip and blueberries.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Let set overnight.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, dump undrained pineapple into pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread onto pineapple layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer. Spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Place butter pats over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: karen's chicken tortilla soup
directions: Place chicken and broth in large pan.
Add creamed corn, chilies, Mexican seasoning and thicken with cornstarch and water (if desired).
Heat through.
Add corn tortillas last.
Garnish with sour cream, grated cheese and green onion (all optional).

title: fish chowder
directions: Rinse fish well.
Boil the fish for about 20 minutes and drain off all the water.
Put the fish back into the pot and fill about 2/3 full.
Add the vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are done. Drain off most of the water, leaving about 1/2 full.
Add the soup and water.
Fry the bacon until crisp. Drain off excess fat. Break into small pieces and add to the chowder just before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Line pan with chopped pecans.
Quarter each biscuit in 4 pieces.
Roll them in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place each piece in Bundt pan building layers.
Between each layer, put nuts and some of the sugar and cinnamon mixture that you have rolled the biscuits in.
After finishing the layers of biscuits, pour the rest of the mixture over the top layer.

title: thick pecan pie
directions: Boil syrup and sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour over beaten eggs. Stir well; add butter and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Bake 50 minutes in 345° oven.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serves 24 to 30.

title: roast leg o' lamb
directions: Combine melted margarine and white wine.
Add tarragon leaves for flavor, if desired. After the roast has been in the oven for 1 hour, baste occasionally with
the mixture.

title: millie's pea salad
directions: Mix all together at the last minute while peas are still frozen.

title: hamburger creole
directions: Cook meat, peppers and onion together for 15 minutes.
Add additional ingredients.
Put in casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
A thin layer of buttered bread crumbs adds to the dish.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: homemade soap
directions: Melt fat and strain.
Dissolve lye in cold water; set aside to cool.
Add fat slowly, constantly stirring mixture.
Mix other ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Stir the whole thing until thick and light colored.
Mix in stainless pans and pour in box lined with cloth.
Mark into pieces of desired size and cut before it hardens.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all items in a bowl.
Put into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one step coffee cake
directions: Beat above until blended, using a wooden spoon.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with onion for approx. 10-15
minutes and drain.
Place in 9 x 13 glass pan, add milk, soup and butter.
mix and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven, spread shredded cheese on top and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: jump crew crab dip
directions: Mix together everything except grated Cheddar cheese.
Place crab mixture into a baking dish.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar on top. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo, eggs and onion. Add to broccoli.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Melt 1/2 stick of margarine into pan; add 1/2 package of Pepperidge Farm herb dressing crumb mix.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pina colada strawberry
directions: Mix together and freeze.
(I blend strawberries and coconut syrup in blender first.)
Scoop into glasses about 1/2 to 3/4 full. Add 7-Up.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix together and cook in unbaked pie shell at 350° until set and brown.

title: old time sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well after each egg.
Add the soda which has been added to the sour cream.
Add flavoring.
Put cream of tartar into a little flour and add to mixture along with as much flour as needed to make a smooth soft dough.
Cool the mixture well before rolling and cutting.
(Can be refrigerated overnight.)
Bake at 350° until lightly browned around edges.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease angel food cake pan.
Place 18 rolls (frozen) tightly together in bottom of pan.
Melt butter; add sugars and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add dry pudding mix, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour over rolls.
Cover tightly with foil and let raise overnight at room temperature.
Remove foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: diet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zesty grilled bread
directions: Slice bread at 1-inch intervals, cutting to, but not through, bottom crust. Using spatulas, place on a large piece of heavy-duty foil.
In mixing bowl, combine cheese, onion, mustard and poppy seed.
Stir in olives and oil and blend well.

Spread mixture evenly on every other bread slice. Wrap loaf loosely in foil. Place on grill rack over medium coals, 10 to 15 minutes or until heated through and cheese begins to melt. Makes 18 to 20 slices.

title: easy chili
directions: Mix all together and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: "stoppin' joes"(sloppy joes)
directions: Heat heavy skillet.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons canola oil. Lightly brown onions and garlic.
Stir in ground sirloin; continue to stir until lightly browned.
Drain.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add 2 bottles chili sauce.
If mixture is not sufficiently "sauce-y," add the third bottle.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and other seasonings to taste.
Use chili powder generously.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve on hamburger rolls; top with Mozzarella cheese, if desired.

title: saltless salt(low calorie dish)
directions: Mix up your own blend of saltless seasoning.
Once you try it you'll retire the salt shaker from your table.
Combine all of the ingredients.
Cover tightly and store in cool dry place.
Use as a table seasoning.
Add to salads, meat, poultry, fish and vegetables.

title: easy fudge
directions: Over low heat, combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth. Add nuts.
Grease pan.
Spread quickly and cool.

title: chocolate chip muffins(a chocoholic's delight)
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and prepare pan.
In a large bowl, add and combine well the first four ingredients.
In smaller bowl, combine remaining ingredients well.
Combine wet and dry mixtures and fold together gently until just mixed.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Dressing:
Melt sugar into oil.
Mix vinegar, salt and pepper into sugar mixture.

title: tidewater coleslaw
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt and pepper. Blend well. In another bowl, combine cabbage and carrots. Pour dressing over vegetables.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Makes 2 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans and put in refrigerator until chilled.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl.
Mix with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in whipped topping. Spread on crust.
Pour 1 cup milk in bowl.
Add puddings; beat for 1 minute (with whisk).
Stir in pumpkin and spices until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Saute onions, ham, green peppers and rice.
Add eggs, soy sauce and salt to other mixture.
Saute.

title: veggie bites
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brush bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with 1 tablespoon of melted butter. Beat egg and water with a fork in a shallow dish.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Wash and if very salty, soak corned beef in cold water for 1 hour.
Put in kettle with bay leaf, garlic, peppercorns and heat slowly, taking off residue as it rises to top of water.
Cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours or until very tender.
When done, take out meat and set aside and in liquid cook cabbage, onions, potatoes, carrots and horseradish.
When vegetables are tender, remove and serve with meat.

title: good bars
directions: Combine margarine, milk, sugar and egg.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat; add coconut, nuts and 1 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole crackers. Cover with filling.
Put another layer of crackers on top, then add icing.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all together with mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: herbed cornish hens
directions: Place hens on a wire rack in a large roasting pan. In a bowl, combine lemon juice, butter, paprika and tsp. thyme, seasoned salt and garlic powder. Pour half over the hens; set the remaining mixture aside for basting. Combine salt, pepper and remaining thyme, seasoned salt and garlic powder, sprinkle over the hens. Bake, uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes. Baste with remaining lemon mixture. Bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally, or until meat is tender and juices run clear.

title: easy italian meat balls
directions: Add some water to bread crumbs to moisten.
Add spices, then ground beef.
Roll into any size.
Bake at 350° from 15 minutes on, depending on how big meat balls are.
When cool, they freeze very well.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: manicotti
directions: Boil noodles and brown sausage; drain.
Cool noodles.
Add sauce to sausage and warm.
Stuff noodles with the 2 cheeses. Pour small amount of sauce in bottom of pan.
Lay noodles in pan. Cover with rest of sauce.
Pour rest of cheese over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Place rolls in Bundt pan to rise overnight.
Sprinkle pudding mix and a little cinnamon over the top.
Melt brown sugar and margarine; pour over the top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: In large saucepan cook zucchini, covered in boiling salt water until tender; boil four or five minutes, drain well and set aside. In same saucepan, cook onions and green pepper in butter until tender but not brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mushrooms, dry sauce mix, water and tomato paste.
Mix well.
Gently stir in zucchini and Mozzarella cheese.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rhubarb party delight
directions: Blend flour, powdered sugar and butter together.
Pat half of mixture firmly in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Reserve rest for topping.
Bake crust 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: partin valley fried chicken
directions: Place flour
into
paper
bag.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces on both
sides.
Place
3 or 4 pieces of chicken in bag and shake well.
Repeat procedure with remaining pieces.
Heat oil and bacon
drippings
in large iron skillet to 325°.
Add chicken and fry
minutes
or
until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: peanut butter pattie treats
directions: Put Karo and sugar in saucepan. Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and stir.
Pour over corn flakes and stir until covered.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper quickly.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Let partially congeal, then fold in last 3 ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until ready.

title: lemony broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. In a small saucepan over low heat cook vegetables in butter until tender, but not browned.
Stir in lemon juice; heat.
Pour this over cooked broccoli in serving dish.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken, covered with water, until it comes off the bone.
Pick off meat and set aside.
Place celery and onion in broth and cook about 15 minutes.
Season broth and add noodles. Add meat and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve with crackers or full-bodied bread, salad and dessert or fruit.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Combine in large bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Add macaroni and toss.
Add shrimp and all other ingredients.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: zesty vegetable salad
directions: In a bowl, combine mushrooms, tomatoes, cucumbers and onion. Add dressing; toss to coat.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: In saucepan, cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in margarine until melted.
Stir in egg and Parmesan cheese.
Spray a 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Press spaghetti mixture into the bottom and up the sides of pie plate, forming a crust.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.

title: dusty's hamburger delight
directions: Put aluminum foil in 11 x 10-inch cooking pan.
Mix hamburger meat with onion soup mix.
Form into patties and place in pan. Slice onions over patties.
Slice potatoes over onions.
Salt and pepper.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in oven on 400° for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar; let stand overnight.
In morning, bring mixture to boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Add jello.
Stir until well mixed.
Put in jars and seal.

title: good fried chicken
directions: Roll chicken (skin and all) in Frying Magic.
Fry in hot oil until cooked and browned.
Then turn oven to 200° and place chicken on a broiler tray.
The excess grease will drop off and it's lickin' good.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, combine milk, water and the 1/4 cup sugar. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, about 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla flavoring until well combined.
Cool.
Whip the whipping cream.
Beat in 1 tablespoon sugar.
Fold cream into pudding. Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with strawberries and strawberry sauce.

title: corn bread(moist type)
directions: Boil the water.
Place the cornmeal in a large mixer bowl. Pour boiling water over meal, slowly mixing, to scald meal.
Add the salt and sugar. Add the eggs one at a time into mixture. Scrape bowl as mixing.
Add the milk and flour alternately. Add the baking powder.
Grease a 10-inch frying pan (or similar container). Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Allow to cool at least 1/2 hour before serving.
When cooked, top will be lightly golden and corn bread will pull away from sides of pan.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
May use some Cheddar cheese (grated) on top, if desired.
Spray dish with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
This and a bowl of fresh cut up fruit is a meal in itself.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts in bottom of greased and floured pan.
Stir cream cheese, margarine and sugar together. Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour in pan on top of coconut and nuts.
Pour cream cheese mixture on top of cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Put the flour and softened margarine in the bottom a pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: parker's corn sticks
directions: Mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix again.
Grease corn stick pans.
Completely fill pan with batter.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes. Then fry in deep fat until brown.

title: banana pudding mix
directions: Mix well and cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Do this until thick.
Pour over bananas and enjoy!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stir-fry cabbage
directions: Melt margarine in a large frypan or Dutch oven.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery.
Add cabbage, then add water and tomatoes.
Cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix ingredients together in medium saucepan for 15 minutes or to boil.
Don't stir once it has started to boil.
After boiling, remove from stove.
Put pan in sink of cold water and beat by hand.
Put butter and vanilla in.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased pan; cool.

title: faye's popcorn balls
directions: Melt oleo.
Pour over marshmallows and cook 1/2 minute.
Stir until melted and pour over popped corn.
Cool a few minutes. Butter hands and form into balls. Add food coloring, if desired, for seasonal look.

title: broiled peaches
directions: Place peaches, cavity side up, in a shallow baking dish.
Dot each cavity with a thin slice of butter.
Sprinkle each peach with cinnamon.
Turn oven to broiler setting at 550°.
Place dish about 6 inches from heat.
Broil for about 7 minutes.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Bake cake according to the directions on the box. Slice in small pieces.
Make the instant pudding according to the directions on box. Slice strawberries in half.
In a large bowl, add a layer of cake, a layer of pudding, a layer of strawberries and a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat until bowl is filled, ending with Cool Whip. Sprinkle nuts over top and place whole strawberries on top of nuts.

title: strawberry shortcake(dominican)
directions: Bake the cake in a 12 x 18-inch aluminum pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let it cool, then slice small holes in the cake.
Mix jello.
Pour about half the jello over the cake into the holes.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Take out.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Add strawberries to the top of the cake.
Preparation time:
approximately 3 hours.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Pare and cube zucchini.
Fry onion in butter until golden. Add tomatoes, mushrooms, basil, seasoning and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add zucchini.
Simmer for 20 more minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Prepare spinach according to package directions; drain. combine spinach and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape into nickel-sized balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: With floured hands, press cookie dough into rectangular cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Let cool down.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Spread on cooled crust.
Top with your favorite fresh fruits. Chill and serve.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with wide noodles mixed all together.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated Italian cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
(If you would like a thicker pizza, use a 9 x 9-inch pan.)

title: south carolina peach cobbler
directions: In a bowl, gently toss peaches with one cup sugar and almond extract; set aside.
Pour butter into a 2-quart baking dish.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and remaining sugar; stir in milk.
Mix well.
Pour evenly over butter (DO NOT STIR).
Top with peach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream.
Easy to make and delicious.

title: german apple cream pie
directions: Mix together and "glob" this on top of apple mixture.
Cook for 20 minutes longer.
Yummy!

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Just before serving, add crackers and mayonnaise.
Tastes even better the next day.

title: crab melt
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat. Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Mix well.
In bowl, fold in crabmeat and pimentos with cheese mixture.

title: spanish rice
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir onion and green pepper in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, salt, pepper and rice. Simmer, uncovered, over low heat, about 15 minutes, until flavors are blended and mixture is hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter, banana and brown sugar sandwich
directions: Put peanut butter on one slice of bread. Lay bananas, cut side up, on peanut butter. Sprinkle with brown sugar and put other slice of bread on. Wrap in wax paper and let sit a couple hours. Eat and enjoy.

title: beef tips
directions: Add salt and pepper to flour before coating meat. Saute beef coated in flour in a small amount of cooking oil. Add red, pepper, cloves, onions, allspice, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon. Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: iced coffee polish style
directions: Combine the sugar and coffee.
Chill several hours.
Place 1/4 cup ice cream in each of 4 serving glasses.
Add 1 1/2 ounces vodka to each glass.
Divide the coffee mixture among the cups and serve topped with whipped cream.

title: old-fashion molasses cookies
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
Add shortening as you would for pastry.
Cut in well.
Add molasses and eggs.
Mix together.
Roll a teaspoonful into a ball and roll in sugar. Place on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press sugar cookie dough into pizza pan and bake.
Cool. Prepare Dream Whip and add cream cheese.
Beat until smooth. Spread on cookie, leaving about 1/2-inch around edge.
Arrange fruit and slice with pizza cutter. Children will love it and you can always choose any fruit you like.

title: mother's molasses cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Let stand for 2 hours (overnight is better) before rolling out and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: beef-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in baking dish and bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, peanuts and salt in 2-quart bowl or dish. Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 4 more minutes on High.
Add butter or margarine and vanilla and blend.
Cook 2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda and blend.
Pour onto buttered foil and spread.
Cool 20 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: white jello
directions: Stirring constantly, bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients. Cool.
Fold in with wire whisk the sour cream, Cool Whip and almond extract.
Pour into a lightly greased mold and chill overnight for best results.

title: tuna balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and make into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 serving.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs and parsley flakes. Mix well. In a 9 x 13-inch lasagna casserole pan, evenly spread 1 cup of pasta sauce. Top with 1/2 of noodles, then spread cheese mixture, then ground beef, then 1 1/2 cups pasta sauce, then Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layering, finishing with Mozzarella cheese. Cover tightly with aluminum foil. Bake 1 hour. Uncover. Bake 15 more minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and mash; add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Mix the ground chuck with the slightly beaten egg, tomato sauce and dry bread or cracker crumbs.
Spread out to about a 10 x 14-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with chopped onion, green pepper, cream cheese, mushroom stems and pieces and grated Longhorn cheese.
Roll up as for jelly roll.

title: molasses crisp cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and molasses, then add all the other sifted dry ingredients.
Chill either overnight or for a couple of hours.
Make into balls.
Dip one side into sugar and press out with fork on cookie sheet.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Slice tomatoes.
Sprinkle with basil, seasoned salt and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with Italian dressing.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add sauce and dressing before serving.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, lime rind, lime juice and sugar substitute with electric mixer on medium speed in large bowl until fluffy, 3 to 4 minutes. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon evenly into prepared graham cracker crust. Chill 4 hours or until the filling is firm. Garnish with the lime slices if desired.

title: mary arrington's dried fruit pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix all ingredients with egg yolks thoroughly. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until filling is getting firm all over except center. (Do not overcook.)
Top with stiffly beaten egg whites to which 3 tablespoons sugar has been added.
Brown in slow oven, about 12 minutes.
(This is Old Heard County recipe.)

title: taco pie
directions: In greased frypan, saute onion and warm vegetarian burger. Turn into greased casserole dish.
Top with taco seasoning and mix lightly.
Add optional chillies.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2 glass baking dish. Combine all dry ingredients. Stir into the squash. Add milk, butter and eggs (one at a time). Pour into dish and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes. Enjoy!!

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream cheese and margarine; blend flour and stir in Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Use back of spoon to flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix lime jello and 2 cups of water.
Allow to gel and add 2 cups grapes.
Allow to congeal thoroughly.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and broken nuts.
Spread on congealed mixture and chill thoroughly.
Mix lemon jello and 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Allow to gel and add crushed pineapple.
Pour over mixture and congeal thoroughly.

title: english trifle
directions: Pinch cake into bite size pieces.
Place in bottom of bowl. Mix Jell-O with water and pour over cake while warm.
Add preserves.
Make pudding with milk.
Add to cake.
Add bananas, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat together sugar, syrup, salt, flour and eggs.
Add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Turn the rounded side of some pecans up.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 1 hour or until filling is just set.
Cool before cutting.
Pie can be baked a day ahead and crust will not become soggy.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and salt.
Add sugar, creaming well.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Fold in flavoring.
Turn into lightly greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix bread and eggs until bread is soaked; place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Then add 1/2 cheese and all cooked sausage.
Mix well and top with rest of the cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: lasts forever play dough
directions: Add food coloring to water or for multi-colors add when kneading.

title: simple, easy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in the top of a double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a generously buttered 8-inch square pan. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge out onto a cutting board; cut into squares.
Store in tightly covered containers.
Makes 49 pieces.

title: pot bellies or taco plate
directions: Heat chili or fix taco meat.
Makes about 8 servings.
First grab a handful of chips; put in a bowl or plate.
Then add about 2 spoonfuls of chili or taco meat.
Sprinkle with cheese, onions and tomatoes.
Top with sour cream.

title: easy spoon bread for two
directions: Set
oven
at
While
heating,
put small pan or Pyrex in oven with butter or margarine.
Remove when good and hot.
Add corn meal to boiling water (may be heated in microwave in pint Pyrex); stir rapidly (will get thick).

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Beat butter or margarine and vanilla until creamy.
Add sugar gradually; beat until fluffy.
Add water.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in oats until blended.
Shape into canes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool. Frost canes with thin confectioners sugar frosting.
Stripe with red food coloring.
Makes 36.

title: oatmeal macadamia muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, soak oatmeal in milk for 30 minutes.
Add butter, egg, sugar and raisins.
Stir until well blended.

title: peanut butter and jelly cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Combine sugars in large mixer bowl.
Add peanut butter and butter; beat until smooth and creamy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until blended.
Refrigerate covered for 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Use handle of wooden spoon or thumb to make large indention in center of each ball. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on cookie sheet until firm enough to lift.
Transfer to wire rack to cool completely, then fill centers.
Yields about 5 dozen cookies.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix ingredients.
Store dry.
Use with boiling water to taste by the cup.

title: lemon lush
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together. Pat in 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
While cake is baking, cook pineapple and sugar until thick.
Punch holes in cake with toothpick and pour pineapple mixture over top. Let cool completely.
Mix milk with pudding and spread on cooled cake.
Let set, then cover cake with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Arrange 1 can sliced pineapple or crushed pineapple, cherries or nuts may be used in skillet.
Pour batter over pineapple mixture and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Turn upside down on cake plate.

title: "death" by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to directions on box.
Cool and crumble 1/2 inch in bottom bowl.
Make pudding.
Layer 1/2 on top of brownies, 1/2 of Cool Whip, 1/2 of Heath bars and 1/2 of nuts, then layer again with remaining ingredients.
End with nuts on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: "waste not, want not" canteloupe drink
directions: Ever wonder what to do with a cantaloupe that is overripe or not sweet enough?
Here's the solution:

title: bunco!
directions: To serve at playing tables:

title: banana-blueberry pie
directions: Be sure pie shell is cool.
Slice bananas to cover bottom of shell.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and whipped topping together. Spread over bananas.
Cover with blueberry pie filling. Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, pepper and onion.
Combine and mix well the rest of the ingredients.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and chill at least overnight.
Will keep several days.

title: vivian's cookie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, eggs and oil. Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Mix together with your hands. Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with Pam or lightly coated with oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, cut and enjoy!

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs. Combine all dry ingredients and add to cream mixture. Stir in 1 cup of candies into dough.
Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Decorate with remaining candies.
I put all the candies in my dough.

title: walnut graham torte
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk and mix well.
Fold in apples and 3/4 cup walnuts.
Spread into three greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake test done.
Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pans to wire racks to cool completely.
Whip the cream and confectioners sugar until stiff; spread between layers and on top of torte.
Sprinkle with remaining walnuts.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Combine water and butter in a saucepan.
Cook at medium heat until butter is melted.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well. Add sugar.
Mix well.
Beat with spoon until frosting is smooth.

title: spice cake
directions: Boil in a large saucepan the margarine, sugar, raisins, water, cinnamon and allspice.
Let cool to room temperature.
Stir in sifted flour and baking soda until batter is smooth.
Add nuts. Bake in a 350° oven in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes, until done.
Frost as desired.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all but oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Cook in iron skillet or heavy pan until soft ball stage.
Mix everything else. Drop on wax paper to cool.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O as per directions until slightly jelled.
Add the marshmallows, pineapple and bananas. Set in refrigerator.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip; spread over pretzel layer. Spread on pie filling.
You can use any flavor pie filling.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening over low heat.
Add brown sugar.
Mix well. Let cool.
Add eggs and blend.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts and chocolate morsels.
Spread in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: perfection
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat, add chocolate bits, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered pans.

title: blueberry grunt
directions: Put blueberries in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Pour pineapple juice and all over blueberries.
Sprinkle cake mix over all that (using all of cake mix), then pecans on top of that, then pour melted butter over this, then sprinkle well with sugar, then bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the onion and celery in oleo.
Combine with remaining ingredients and bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Then bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes more to brown.

title: dried beef chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with beef.
Add chicken breasts and put 1 slice of bacon on each breast.
Mix together sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Cover with foil.

title: handy wipes
directions: Cut Bounty paper towels in half horizontally, remove paper core.
Put water, baby oil and baby shampoo in container.
Place half roll of Bounty towels in and cover.
Wait 2 hours, turn upside-down.
Wait 2 hours more.

title: grilled ham steak
directions: Use center cut steaks cut 3/4-inch thick.
Place steak on aluminum foil.
Fold sides up around steak.
Put honey, mustard and brown sugar on each side of steak.
Rub these ingredients together on both sides.
Place on grill.
Turn over a couple of times and cook until lightly browned good on both sides.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Simmer with spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles.
Layer noodles, then sauce, then Ricotta, then Mozzarella.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well (add one at a time, beating well after each addition).
Blend in the lemon juice, rind and vanilla.
Pour into chilled crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and let sit at room temperature for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel gold bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, mayonnaise and vanilla with mixer; add flour and baking soda.
Set aside 1 cup of batter. Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk over low heat; pour over cooled batter and sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon reserved batter by teaspoon over nuts. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix together in saucepan the first 3 ingredients.
Heat to boiling and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
Stir.
Pour into buttered pan or drop by teaspoons on waxed paper or sprinkle nuts on waxed paper; pour candy and roll as jelly roll.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Cover with Swiss cheese.
Add 1/2 cup hot water.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs and liquid.
Beat until mix begins to thicken a little.
Beat in pudding.
Stir in apples and pecans. Pour batter into well greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes, depending on oven or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: stuffed quahogs
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 7 ingredients until blended.
Cook quahogs until they steam open, then cut them into small pieces; add to first mixture.
Save the shells and put a little oil in each shell, then fill with batter.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: all season rice
directions: Combine ingredients in 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Cover and cook on High (Maximum power), 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 10 minutes or until all broth is absorbed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked apples
directions: Take the apples. Cut a hole in top, removing stems.
Put some butter, brown sugar and cinnamon on each apple placing in a round baking dish. Bake at 350° uncovered until apples are done.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add, alternating with milk. Bake 80 minutes at 325° in greased and floured, large tube pan. Serve sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Slowly beat all ingredients with a mixer just to blend.
Chill in a cooled baked pie shell at least 2 hours.

title: jambalaya
directions: Put oil, chicken and sausage in a pan and saut. Once the chicken is white, add enough water to reach the top of your meat. Put to cook on a medium fire and cover for 40 minutes, add seasoning to taste and add water when needed. After 40 minutes, add Kitchen Bouquet and cook for another 5 minutes. Take fire off the meat once you cook it for 45 minutes. Put rice to cook separately; once the rice is done, add the rice to the meat and stir together and you are done.

title: caldo verde(kale soup)
directions: Fry sausage; drain fat and set aside 2 tablespoons of fat. Cook beans as usual.
Add sausage.
Place remaining ingredients into a large kettle.
Add the sausage drippings and 10 cups of water.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours, until the kale is tender. Add potatoes and cook until tender; add water as needed.
If you like thick soup, mash either the potatoes or beans.
Add the bean and sausage mixture to the kale soup.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with thick slices of bread.

title: pan-broiled venison
directions: Tenderize meat (preferably back strap) with meat cleaver. Sprinkle with powdered tenderizer.
Let set for 30 minutes. Season meat with onion salt, garlic salt or powder and black pepper.
Melt one stick margarine in electric or deep skillet or Dutch oven.
Add dry or liquid Worcestershire sauce to taste, approximately 2 tablespoons.
Cover meat with water.
Simmer with lid on about half an hour.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Thin if desired with a little water or milk.
(I cook it in the microwave.)

title: double-quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Measure flour.
Stir sugar and half of flour and salt into yeast.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in rest of flour until smooth.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise until double in size, about 30 minutes.

title: nutty apple muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given. Mix well. Pour into muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. May be frozen.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Peel carrots, onions and cucumbers.
Remove seed from cucumbers and green peppers.
Grate all vegetables finely or chop in food processor.
Squeeze juice from vegetables, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Put 3 tablespoons juice in small saucepan and sprinkle gelatin over juice.
Heat slowly until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour over vegetables, adding salt, sugar and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate until set.
Stir when ready to spread on bread or crackers.
(If too stiff, add more mayonnaise.)

title: hobo bread
directions: Bring coffee to a boil; remove from heat.
Add baking soda and raisins.
Cover; allow to stand overnight.
In the morning, preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 3 (1-pound) coffee cans. Add sugars, flour, nuts and salt to coffee-raisin mixture.
Mix well.
Bake for 65 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in cans before removing.
Serve with cream cheese or butter.

title: m-m-m good brownies
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Mix in chocolate syrup.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour.
Put mixture in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, spread with chocolate icing.
Cut in squares.
May be topped with nuts.

title: pears noires
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan large enough to hold pears upright.
Cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Cover tightly and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carlos' chili
directions: Fry hamburger and onions.
Put into pot the hamburger mixture, chili beans, pinto beans, tomatoes, onions, A.1. sauce, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and chili powder.
Cook over simmering heat for 3 1/2 hours.
At about 1/2 hour before done, put in diced bell peppers.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Defrost broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crunchy vegetable spread
directions: Place vegetables in colander to drain.
Beat cream cheese and lemon juice until smooth.
Stir in vegetables.
Add pepper and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Yields 2 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Form into ball.
May roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in foil until served.

title: chocolate fillers
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar and salt.
Blend in flour and oats until fine.
Press about 2/3 mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat milk in a saucepan.
Stir in chips.
Spread over oat mix.
Sprinkle with rest of crumbs.
Press lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until light golden brown.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
chicken,
remove
from
bone.
Layer
chicken and broccoli
in
casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, broth,
salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Melt margarine and mix with crumbled Ritz crackers. Sprinkle over
top
of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and slightly brown.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: walnut jewel salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in hot water.
Drain pineapple, saving syrup.
Combine syrup and lemon juice with cold water to measure 1 2/3 cups liquid.
Add to jello.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken slightly.
Fold in walnuts, celery, cranberries and drained pineapple.
Turn into an oiled 1 1/2-quart mold and chill until firm, at least 4 hours.
Unmold onto lettuce.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions on package.
Cool and cut horizontally.
Spread filling over bottom half.
Replace top half and cover with strawberries and glaze mixture.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix together last 5 ingredients.
Pour mixture over vegetables and marinate in refrigerator.
Keeps for weeks!

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add buttermilk.
Stir.
Knead lightly.
Roll out on floured board.
Spread 1/2 pound bulk sausage on bread.
Roll as for a jelly roll.
Wrap in wax paper and place in freezer.
When ready to cook, slice while they are partially frozen; place on cookie sheet and cook at 350° until lightly browned.

title: czech cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks and beat well.
Add the flour gradually, mixing well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread 1/2 batter into a greased 8 x 8 pan and top with preserves.
Cover with remaining batter and bake 1 hour or until top crust is light brown at 325 degrees.
Cool well before cutting.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as stated on package.
Do not overcook.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
Chop onion, bell pepper and tomatoes in small pieces, then add seasonings, dressing and tomato sauce. Mix well.
Add spaghetti, a little at a time, and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.

title: cheesy vegetable saute
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Saute peppers, onion, garlic and basil until crisp-tender.
Stir in tomatoes.
Place on ovenproof serving platter.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Broil until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes (or longer for softer texture) before cutting.
Keep chilled in refrigerator.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and fruit, if desired.

title: dream puffs
directions: Blend oleo and 1/2 cup sugar over moderate heat.
Beat the egg and add other 1/2 cup sugar.
Combine with oleo mixture.
Add chopped dates and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Grease hands.
Roll mixture into balls and dip in coconut.

title: gram's irish soda bread
directions: Stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add melted butter and mix.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed.
Combine buttermilk, egg and baking soda.
Make a well in center of the batter.
Pour liquid in and stir into flour mixture.
Place in a large iron frying pan, well buttered.
Use a knife to make a cross on the top. Moisten with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for an hour or until golden brown and shrinks from the side of pan.

title: green chili dip
directions: Mix diced green chiles and package of Cheddar cheese.
Beat 2 eggs with milk.
Pour over cheese and chile mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a glass pie plate.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(The point is that as long as you follow the basic principles of tomato/sweetener/vinegar/sweet liquid, you can create your own Sweet and Sour Sauce.)

title: lillie's butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees for 10 minutes or lightly brown.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes almost through.
Add butter, sesame seed, chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Roll in squares of foil twice to drip proof.
Cook 1 hour on grill.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over beef and onion in plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomato slices and sprinkle on cheese.
Continue baking until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
(Pat says this dish promotes flatulence.)

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, garlic salt, salt, onion and pepper. Heat in broiler taco sauce, chilies and soups.
Mix soup mixture with hamburger.
Alternate layers of mixture and Doritos and cheese.
Top with Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except fruit, and refrigerate. Serve chilled.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: date nut candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and cream of tartar until all dissolved. Add dates and cook until forms a ball in cold water.
Beat and add nuts.
Roll in damp towel.
When cold, slice.

title: *lentil soup 1
directions: Wash lentils and drain.
Place all ingredients in saucepan. Mix well.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Add a few drops of red wine vinegar to each bowl just before serving.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix pudding, sugar, egg yolks, vanilla, nutmeg and milk in a large bowl and beat at low speed for about 1 minute.
Fold in egg whites.
Chill.

title: broccoli-mushroom saute
directions: In large skillet, melt butter; saute onion until tender.
Stir in broccoli, mushrooms, garlic salt and pepper; saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat 5 to 7 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender, stirring frequently.

title: master cookie mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening and add chocolate chips and pecans.
Store.

title: sour milk waffles
directions: Beat whites until stiff and fold into other ingredients that have been mixed together.
These melt in your mouth and are as tender as a mother's love.

title: german chess pie
directions: Mix these ingredients, except pie shells, and keep beating as you pour into shells to keep mixture from settling.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: paella stew
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes until shrimp are done.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Add salt and vanilla; then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Place in cold oven and bake at 275°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool in pan.

title: barb's cheesecake
directions: Mix together.
Press with fork or floured fingers into 8-inch square pan on bottom and on sides.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Make corn bread mix.
Chop celery and onion (very fine) and parboil until tender.
Add this to corn bread (cooked and broken into small pieces).
Add eggs and poultry seasoning to taste.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add turkey broth.
(This should be of a soft consistency, but not watery.)
Put into well-greased pan (preferably cast-iron skillet) and bake at 400° until brown (usually 25 minutes).

title: meatball hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours. Shape meatballs and drop into sauce. Simmer 30 to 40 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 50 meatballs.

title: hot caramel sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the whipping cream and sugar. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 10 to 12 minutes until mixture is slightly thickened.
Stir in corn syrup, butter and vanilla.

title: joe's favorite mile-high coconut pie
directions: Cream, blend, beat and cook together on stove on medium heat, stirring constantly, until it looks like pancake batter. Add a little milk if it seems too thick.
Finish cooking in slightly browned pie crust in preheated oven at 350° about 30 minutes. Remove and top with meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut and return to oven until slightly brown.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in a medium saucepan.
Add rice and stir until browned.
Add broth and salt.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cook covered for 20 minutes.
Rice will be fluffy and liquid should be completely absorbed.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Marinate beef in dressing for 1 day.
Marinate vegetables also.
Cook on skewers over charcoal for about 1/2 hour.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage, pepper and onion in soup pot (drain off grease).
Add and simmer the tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, cubes and bay leaf.
