After the soup has simmered 15 minutes, add 1/2 cup shell macaroni or more if you like the soup thick.
I usually add a little tomato juice as I like more liquid in my soup.
This is good topped with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: ground beef in gravy
directions: Cook ground beef in a frypan until browned.
Pour off fat. Stir in flour and salt.
Slowly stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Makes 2 servings, about 2/3 cup each.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil on very low heat. Remove.
Add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Stir well. Spoon onto wax paper. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: a meal in one pork chops casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except pork chops.
Place these ingredients in baking dish.
Salt and pepper the pork chops and put them on top of ingredients.
Then place the dish in the oven and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's pear pie
directions: Slice fresh peaches into unbaked pie shell.
Mix flour, sugar and cream.
Pour over pears.
Sprinkle with lemon peel, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 60 minutes at 375°.

title: saltine cake
directions: Spread Cool Whip on cake.
Drain crushed pineapple and place on top of Cool Whip and then frozen coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel together in separate bowl.
Next, layer in 3-quart dish.
Put meat first, soup mixture next, Doritos, then cheese.
Repeat layers.
Finish with Doritos and cheese on top.
Cook at 325° about 15 to 20 minutes or until heated.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine and stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn while stirring.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in 1/2 cup sour cream and 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker pie crusts. Chill overnight.
Can put fresh fruit (diced peaches, blueberries) in pie shell before filling.

title: fruit juice breakfast shake
directions: Break bananas into small pieces and put in the blender with remaining ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into 2 (12 ounce) glasses and serve.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Boil water; add jello and let cool.
Add sour cream and crushed pineapple, drained.
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into mold. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Drain pineapple, add to this Cool Whip, pecans and can of oranges.
Mix all of this with Eagle Brand mixture.
You can top with cherries or mix them in.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer in deep dish:

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Hollow out potatoes into bowl and save skin.
Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon mixture back into shells.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: cold chicken curry salad
directions: Make this at least 3 hours in advance and chill.
Toss chicken, celery and lemon juice and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in sour cream, mayonnaise and curry powder. Carefully fold in 4 sliced hard-boiled eggs.
Cover and refrigerate.
To serve, spoon into lettuce cups and top with more egg slices.
Garnish with fresh parsley (optional).
Serves 12.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until soft.
Place in buttered casserole.
Melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper and blend.
Add milk slowly until sauce thickens.
Cut cheese into cubes; add to sauce.
Stir constantly until cheese has melted.
Pour cheese sauce over macaroni and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana scotch muffins
directions: Puree banana in blender.
In medium bowl, combine banana, egg, sugar, milk, oil and vanilla.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir banana mixture into dry ingredients with butterscotch chips until just blended.
Spoon into well-greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Bake in 400° oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar together until smooth on low speed. Add Cool Whip. Beat until blended. Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with cherry pie filling. Cover and refrigerate until chilled, about 1 hour.

title: pepper cheese ball
directions: Mix the cheeses and peppers together.
Using plastic wrap, form into ball.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unwrap and roll cheese ball in crumbs or nuts.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving with crackers.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix and beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°; lower heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.

title: hershey's sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Combine baking chocolate, butter or oleo and boiling water. In a small bowl, stir until chocolate and butter or oleo are melted.
Combine brown sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add chocolate mixture, beating until thoroughly combined.
Blend eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Add the very warm water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Add the egg and 1/2 cup white flour. Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup white flour (or enough to make a thick batter).
Cover and let rise about 1hour. Stir down and fill muffin pans 1/2 full.
(Raisins, bananas, apples or other fruits may be added before filling pans.) Let rise about 1 hour. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: green bean salad
directions: Early in the day in 12-inch skillet over high heat in 1/2-inch of boiling water, heat green beans to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until beans are tender.

title: no bake cherry pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix together.
Place in pie crust and top with cherry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over 3 cups quick Quaker oatmeal or 4 1/2 cups generic oatmeal.
You can add nuts, raisins or dates.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chicken & rice casserole
directions: Prepare Minute Rice according to directions on box and add celery at the same time as rice.
Mix in the soup, mayonnaise, onion, and chicken.
If too dry, add 1/3 to 1/2 cup water.	Pour into a greased 9 inch x 13 inch vessel.
Top with 1 cup crushed flakes and pour 1/2 stick of melted butter on top.	Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first three ingredients in baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix ground beef, whole tomatoes, juice, chopped onions, chopped pepper tops, salt, pepper, garlic salt and onion salt. Add Minute rice; stuff peppers with mixture. Cook in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Can use sausage.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
While the chops brown, peel potatoes. In a 8-inch square dish, slice potatoes thin and place single layer in dish.
Sprinkle flour over potatoes, salt and pepper. Make at least two layers of potatoes, three is better.
Pour enough milk to just cover potatoes.
Dot several pieces of margarine on top.
Place chops on top of all.
Cover with foil tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: streusel raspberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease or paper line 12 (2 1/2 inch) muffin cups. Prepare pecan streusel topping; set aside. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder. In small bowl, combine milk, butter and egg until blended. Stir into flour mixture just until moistened. Spoon half of batter into muffin cups. Divide raspberries among cups, then top with remaining batter. Sprinkle pecan streusel topping over tops. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden and wooden toothpick inserted in centers comes out clean. Remove from pan. Makes 12 muffins.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients except almonds.
Chill.
Right before serving, top with dressing and toss to coat.
Sprinkle on almonds.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to boil, add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add water and chill until slightly firm.
Fold in cheese, nuts and whipped topping.
Refrigerate in a tight container.
This makes a large salad.

title: cinnamon apple oat bread
directions: Mix
flour,
baking powder, cinnamon and salt.	Combine egg, egg
whites, milk, sugar and oil.
Add to flour mixture; stir until moistened.
Stir in cereal, apples and nuts.	Pour into well-greased
x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or	until
tester
comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove
from pan
and
cool
completely.
Makes 18 (1/2 inch) slices.

title: greek salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; chill 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
When ready to serve, toss with salad. Serves 6.

title: jodi's jello
directions: Dissolve lemon jello with 2 cups hot water.
Let cool, but not set.
Whip cream; add softened cream cheese and pineapple and blend together.
Add to cooled lemon jello.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Clean chicken; cut into pieces.
Add ingredients minced together.
Put in pan and simmer about an hour or until chicken is tender.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and spices together 3 times. Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients and tomato soup, alternately, in small amounts.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into small greased tube pan or loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 24 hours before cutting.

title: apple annie's poppy seed dressing(fresh fruit dressing)
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, dry mustard, salt and vinegar.
Mix well with a wire whisk.
Add oil slowly, whisking until thick and creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and whisk well to combine.

title: basic layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter thoroughly.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavoring. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
I make 6 layers out of this, but you can just do 3 layers.
When baking 6 layers, reduce the baking time to 15 minutes each.

title: baked scallop timbales
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in well-greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm in the center and brown.

title: baked mochi
directions: Mix first five ingredients, then pour into greased
9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool in pan overnight, then cut into 1-inch squares and roll in potato starch.

title: cherry bake
directions: In 8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch or approximate round baking dish, place cherry pie filling in bottom.
Cover with cake mix.
Melt margarine and over mix and sprinkle pecan pieces on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mother's coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baked pie shell.
Dot with butter and bake at 375° until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and vanilla and spread on crust.
Mix chocolate pudding mix and 1 1/3 cups milk and spread.
Mix vanilla pudding mix and 1 1/3 cups milk and spread.

title: cheesy catfish
directions: Combine cheese, flour, salt, pepper and paprika in a bowl. Mix egg and milk.
Dip fish in egg mixture and then in cheese mixture to coat well.
Place aluminum foil in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and place fish on foil.
Pour margarine over fish and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fresh pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice very thin (1/16-inch).
Place in stainless steel or glass container with finely chopped onion and green pepper.
Toss with salt and mustard seed and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain off as much juice as possible, without losing mustard seed.

title: spicy black-eyed peas
directions: Combine black-eyed peas and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Drain; set aside. Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until crisp-tender.
Add peas, tomato and next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until peas are tender, stirring occasionally.
Transfer to a serving dish; sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Yield:
12 servings.
Each serving contains 5.4 grams protein and 0.6 grams fat.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add flour and vanilla.
Add crushed potato chips.
Drop by small teaspoons on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk in large mixing bowl.
Add the pudding mix and mix until it is mixed well.
Fold the whipped topping into this mixture until it is well blended.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers on the bottom of large deep dish, then a layer of sliced bananas. Cover with half of pudding mixture.
Repeat another layer to dress it up, then add some vanilla wafer crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until you serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: delicious hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then add 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce; mix again.
Bake at 300° until it bubbles. Serve with crackers.
Keep dip warm.

title: quick bouillabaisse
directions: Drain and flake crab meat reserving liquid.
Combine with tomatoes, the liquid and rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles and drain.
Brown meat, onion, parsley, oregano, salt, basil and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon small amount of meat sauce to pan bottom of 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Layer noodle, cheeses and sauce.
Bake 30 minutes until bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cranberry juice punch
directions: Combine chilled juices and sweetener.
Add ice cubes.

title: shrimp and crabmeat quiche
directions: Separate triangles of dinner rolls.
Place 7 triangles in quiche dish or 9-inch pie pan.
Bring together to form crust. Combine remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl and mix well. Handle crab meat gently.
Pour into crust.
Roll out remaining dinner rolls and cut in strips.
Place on top to form top crust. Bake at 325° for approximately 60 minutes until knife comes out clean when inserted in center.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes; coat with flour, salt and pepper to taste. Fry in vegetable oil until tender.

title: ham loaf
directions: Braise brown sugar.
Pour 1/2 of braise over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Pour remaining braise and bake another 1/2 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip brownies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Beat together peanut butter and margarine until well blended.
Beat in sugars until well mixed. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture until well blended. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ambrosia pudding
directions: In a bowl, blend pudding and milk according to package directions.
Add honey, orange peel and vanilla.
Fold in the whipped cream.
In individual dishes, layer half of the pudding, banana slices, orange sections, coconut and almonds.
Repeat the layers.
Chill.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter.
Chop or grate all vegetables finely.
Add stock, soda and paprika.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cut-up cheese and white sauce.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Add salt if needed.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add pecans and grated carrots.
Bake 3 layers in 9-inch pans at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Mix coconut and milk; spread over bars and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Frost with the melted chocolate chips.
Cut in bars for serving.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Make pastry for two crust pie of desired size.
Line pie pan.

title: strawberry preserves supreme
directions: *This recipe works better when you make only 4 cups at a time.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a greased 10 x 15-inch pan at 275° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add the egg.
Add Butterfinger pieces, salt, soda and flour.
Mix all together by hand.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Mash lightly with fork.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup crumbs and 1/2 stick butter.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top; pour melted 1/2 stick butter over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower-broccoli medley
directions: Separate cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces. Combine all vegetables in a large mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients, except bacon; add vegetables gently.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Toss vegetables several times during the marinating period.
Garnish with crumbed bacon.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican chickena delightful variation of king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken and debone it.
Grate cheese.
In sauce pan, heat soups and chilies.
Tear tortillas in quarters.
Layer tortillas, chicken, sauce, and cheese.
If you like, put 1/2 cup of broth to soup.
Bake at 350° F. for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, then add well beaten eggs and milk. Sift flour and soda; add to mixture.
Beat well.
Add walnuts; flour raisins and add to mixture.
Beat all well.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° until done.

title: plain rhubarb pie
directions: Beat egg; add sugar, flour and rhubarb.
Spread over lower crust of 9-inch pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Put on top crust and bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for about another 25 or 30 minutes.

title: the ultimate peanut butter cookie
directions: Drizzle over chocolate.
Spread, cut and eat.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix and cook for 2 hours or until thick.
Put in jars while hot.

title: jello pretzel dessert
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar and pretzels.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake (with oil)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan or a bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the butter, oil, both sugars, eggs and vanilla until very creamy.
Mix cream of tartar, baking soda, flour and salt.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed butter mixture until blended.

title: very creamy corn
directions: Put all ingredients into a crock-pot and slow cook for three hours.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix egg and buttermilk in a shallow dish.
Mix flour, cornmeal and salt in a shallow dish.
Working in batches, dip tomato slices into egg mixture, allowing excess to drip back into dish. Coat with flour mixture.
Fry in hot oil at 375° in a large heavy skillet until browned, turning once with tongs.
Fry in a single layer with space between slices.
Transfer to paper towels to drain.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze. This keeps well.

title: breakfast sausage and egg souffle
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Combine eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt in bowl.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Chill, covered, overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except morsels.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Fold in morsels.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes before removing.

title: homemade cocoa mix
directions: Stir all together.
Store in airtight container.

title: noodle and cottage cheese
directions: Place water in a pot.
Bring water to a boil.
Add 1/2 package egg noodles.
Cook for 8 minutes.
Drain noodles; return to pot. Add cottage cheese.
Mix until well coated.
Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar to taste.
Makes about 4 to 6 servings.

title: alyeska almond chicken
directions: Toss bread cubes with melted butter. Set aside. Mix remaining ingredients. Spoon into 10 x 6 baking dish. Top with bread cubes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Sprinkle 2 boxes yellow Jiffy cake mix evenly over pumpkin. Drizzle 1 stick melted margarine over dry cake mix.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate-apricot tea ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Chop apricots and almonds. In medium bowl combine apricots, 1/4 c. of the almonds and chocolate morsels. Unroll breadstick dough into 2 rectangles on 12 x 18 inch cutting board; do not separate dough. Using lightly floured rolling pin, lightly roll dough to press seams together. Spread each dough rectangle with 1 Tbsp of the preserves; top evenly with chopped apricot mixture. Starting at longest side of each rectangle, roll up dough, jelly-roll fashion; press seams together to seal. Place rolls, seam sides down, on 13 inch baking stone or cookie sheet. Join ends together to form 1 large ring. Using knife, cut from outside of ring to within 1 inch of inside of ring making cuts at perforations in dough. Turn each section on its side so filling shows. Bake 25-30 minutes or until golden. Remove to cooling rack. In small bowl, combine powdered sugar and milk; drizzle over warm coffee cake. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/4 c. almonds. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: mayonnaise for lettuce
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Stir into beaten eggs.
Add salt, vinegar and water.
Cook until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Cool and serve.

title: apache bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add boiling water and bacon drippings. Form into small rolls and wrap in green cornhusks.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 12 individual breads.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in very thin strips; trim off excess fat.
Brown meat and mushrooms in butter.
Add onions.
Combine soup, tomato paste and seasoning.
Add to meat mixture.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Thicken gravy if desired.
Serve in rings of fluffy hot rice.
Garnish with parsley.

title: cocktail sausage appetizers
directions: Prepare early in morning to achieve best flavor.
Put sausage in crock-pot set on low heat.
In saucepan, bring all remaining ingredients to boil and pour over sausages.
Cook in crock-pot on low all day.
Serve hot with Club crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients. Pour into pastry-line pie pan.
Top with top crust.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: candy (butterscotch or chocolate, etc.)
directions: Mix margarine, milk and sugar in skillet and bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Add pudding and mix well.
Stir in oats and let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon out with teaspoon onto waxed paper. Allow to cool.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: In
a large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat. Add onion. Cook until golden. Add cabbage and cook until tender-crisp. Stir in noodles and remaining ingredients until blended.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raisin carrot muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger. Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Separately combine undrained pineapple, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on rack outside of muffin tin.

title: purple hull pea jelly
directions: Boil
hulls
from peas until tender, then strain juice. Mix juice with Sure-Jell and bring to boil.
Add sugar.
Bring to boil
again and boil 15 minutes.
Set aside for 5 minutes. Skim. Pour into jars.
Seal as desired.

title: picante sauce
directions: Combine all and cook slowly until tomatoes are done, 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: randy's fish meal
directions: In my travels, I have found a marvelous diet that I would like to share.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot with tight fitting lid. Bake in 275° oven for 5 hours without opening the lid.

title: lazy peach pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pan over 1 stick of margarine.
Pour 1 can sliced peaches over mixture in pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: tonya's pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry shell; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until toothpick is inserted and it comes out clean.
Cool and garnish with Cool Whip.
They'll ask for another piece!

title: fluffy angel pie
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice. Chill until partially jelled. Add peel.
Whip milk until thick. Fold in jello and add fruit cocktail. Spoon into dessert dishes and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook all ingredients together until clear.
Cool.
Pour over sliced fresh peaches in cooked pie crust.

title: bread dip(a popular request for all parties)
directions: Cut up all meat into small 1/2 x 1/2-inch chunks.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Hollow out one loaf of bread, pressing toward remaining sides of loaf the fresh bread, making a bowl/boat shape. Fill with mixture and chill.
Cube remaining bread and other loaf to arrange around filled loaf when serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and put in baking dish.
Dice onions and put them on top of potatoes.
Put asparagus on top of that.
Canned or fresh can be used (uncooked works fine).
Dot with butter. Cover tightly and cook at least 45 minutes in oven at 350° or until potatoes are done.
Lay cheese on top and let melt before serving.

title: casserole of leftover meat
directions: Cut leftover meat into chunks.
Parboil potatoes and onions. Add tomato soup to gravy and place all ingredients in baking dish. Top with chunks of cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: spanish rice pronto
directions: Melt fat in skillet. Add onion, green pepper and rice right from the box. Cook and stir over high heat until lightly browned. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, all the time the rice needs to take all the flavor in.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Mix and let stand 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a pan of water.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Jell-O, pineapple juice and lemonade.
Put ginger ale in last, right before serving.
Makes approximately 1 gallon of punch.

title: crispy pie
directions: Melt together the peanut butter and honey for 30 seconds.
Add Rice Krispies cereal and stir together.
Pat into 9-inch pie pan. Put in freezer for 10 minutes.
Mix instant chocolate pudding with milk.
Pour mixture into cooled shell and refrigerate.
Makes about 6 servings.
Excellent.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together; add onions and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot shortening about 3 inches deep.
Cook until golden brown.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a rolling boil and cook for about 10 minutes.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Stir in butter and cool to room temperature.
Stir in sour cream and pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream and garnish with lemon twists.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In a large bowl of electric mixer, at medium speed, beat together oil, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla until thoroughly combined.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Fold in chopped apple, pecans and raisins.
(I sometimes omit the nuts.) Turn into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt chocolate.
Mix oil, chocolate & sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Stir and place in covered bowl in refrigerator for several hours.
Roll into balls, dip in confectioners sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 5-8 minutes.

title: shrimp-artichoke-black olive
directions: Cook shrimp; place on ice and chill overnight.
Put the mustard, salt, pepper, garlic and red wine vinegar in bowl; whisk. Gradually add oil, etc.
Marinate a few hours.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red cinnamon rings
directions: Peel, core out seeds and slice cucumbers in 1/4-inch thick rings or 2-inch chips.
Soak 2 gallons of cucumbers for 24 hours in lime and 8 1/2 quarts water.
Drain and wash well.
Soak 3 hours in ice water.
Put together 1 cup vinegar, alum and red food coloring.
Add water to cover.
Put on stove and simmer 2 hours. Do not boil.
Drain well and discard solution.
Make syrup of remaining ingredients.
Cover cucumbers with syrup.
For next 2 mornings, drain off syrup and heat.
Pour over cucumbers; do not boil.
On third morning, heat all and put in jars.
Seal.
Do not boil.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Heat to boiling, canned milk, water, cheese and butter.
Mix in bread crumbs, salt and onion.
Fold in eggs and macaroni.
Put in 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm.

title: sore throat medicine
directions: Put ingredients into a pot and bring to a boil.
Drink 3 tablespoons every 6 hours as hot as you can stand it.
Put in a jar and place it in the refrigerator.

title: mexican vegetable dip
directions: Cover ingredients with vinegar and water mix.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Pour off some liquid before serving with tortilla chips.

title: new orleans lace cookies
directions: Mix together the melted butter, egg and vanilla and blend in dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on a foil-lined cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cookies are better if thin.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove carefully.

title: momma's gingerbread
directions: Mix wet ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add dry to wet slowly, mixing well.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, about 35 minutes.

title: hard rolls
directions: Soften yeast with 1/4 cup lukewarm water; add remaining water. Add sugar and shortening.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well.
Add yeast and egg whites; mix through.
Add remaining flour and salt to make soft dough.
Rise once; punch down and let rise again.
Brush with egg yolk diluted with water.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Clean chicken.
Spray roasting pan with Pam.
Place chicken (breast up) in roasting pan.
Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper, garlic and paprika to taste.
Douse with white wine Worcestershire sauce.
Pour honey all over the chicken.
Cover pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar, flour, cherries and all the juice in a saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Stir in jello.
Let cool and add bananas.
Pour into shells.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bananas.
Chill until ready to serve.
Just before serving, fold in bananas.

title: cheesy bacon skins
directions: Layer 3 paper towels on a plate.
Arrange bacon slices on paper towels, and cover with another paper towel.
Microwave on High for 3 to 6 minutes.
Cool and crumble.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, onion and horseradish.
Mix well.
Divide mixture into 8 equal portions.
Spread 1 portion onto each potato skins.
Sprinkle with bacon crumbs and cheese.
Microwave on Medium for 3 1/2 to 7 minutes.
Serve with additional sour cream if desired.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place 1 strip of ham and 1 strip of cheese on each chicken breast.
Spread with a little mustard.
Starting with short end, roll chicken breast (jelly roll fashion).
Secure with toothpick. Place in greased glass pan.
Butter tops.
Place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour; baste occasionally.
Tops should be light brown (can be prepared ahead but not baked).

title: cranberry cooler
directions: Pour 1/4 cup cranberry juice over ice in each of 6 glasses; stir in 1/2 cup wine.
Garnish with orange slice.
Makes 6 servings (about 3/4 cup each).

title: oatmeal chocolate mint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together first seven ingredients. Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to first seven ingredients.
When beaten smooth add oatmeal and mix well.
Drop cookies 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine; add to powdered sugar, pineapple juice and vanilla.
Beat by hand until it is a creamy spread.
Pour into dish.
Chill for 15 minutes or until firm.

title: julie's pig in the blankets
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Roll each half around a sausage. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Enjoy with mustard.

title: chicken stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased baking dish.
Bake in oven 30 minutes at 350°.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown meat with first 3 seasonings.
Drain beef.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain. Mix sour cream and onions together.
Butter casserole dish and layer ingredients in the following order:
noodles, beef mixture and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle cheese and quartered garlic on top.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple dream cloud
directions: Open pineapple and drain very good. Mix all ingredients together; add dry Jell-O to mixture. Mix and put in a large bowl; top with nuts, then chill overnight. Contains 150 calories per serving. Serving size is 1 cup. Fat per serving is 3 grams.

title: cabbage noodles
directions: Cook all ingredients until well done in 1 1/2 quarts water. Use more water, if needed.

title: poppy seed dressing (for fruit)
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Add onion juice.
While blending, add oil and blend as well as possible.
Fold in poppy seed carefully.
This dressing will keep indefinitely in the refrigerator.
It is a marvelous compliment for fresh fruit as it takes the tartness away without covering the fresh taste.

title: baked rice
directions: Combine the ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes, then covered for an additional 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
This is a good side dish and simple to make.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream
butter;
gradually
add
cup sugar, beating until light
and
fluffy.
Add water and vanilla.
Beat well. Gradually stir in flour and fold in pecans; chill.
Break off dough by teaspoonfuls
and
shape into circles or 2-inch crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Remove immediately
from cookie sheet and cool about 3 to 4 minutes. Coat
with
powdered
sugar.
Yield: 6 dozen. This recipe may be doubled.
These
are also good with almond flavoring substituted for vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli and salt and drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Top with finely grated Pepperidge Farm herb seasoned stuffing (1/2 bag) mixed with 1 stick melted margarine.
Press down and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, 11 x 6 1/2-inch. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: apple salad
directions: Peel apples and cut into chunks.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to apples.
Chill and serve.

title: curry dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Chill and serve as a dip for fresh cut vegetables or seafood.
Makes 1 cup.

title: jalapeno salsa
directions: Boil jalapenos and tomatoes for about 20 minutes.
Blend garlic and salt together.
Blend for about 3 minutes; blend the tomatoes and jalapenos with the garlic and the salt and pour it in a bowl and it's ready to serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring water, broccoli and onion to boiling and boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer until cheese melts. Add half and half and oleo and heat to boiling.
Combine flour and water; add to hot mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: chicken italian style
directions: Saute onions and olive oil in large skillet.
Add chicken and brown slightly on both sides.
Then pour spaghetti sauce, wine or beer, garlic, salt and pepper into skillet.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over pasta of choice.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9x13 pan, layer ingredients as follows:

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook celery and onion in chicken broth until tender. Break toasted bread into pieces. Add broth with celery and onion to bread. Mix well. Add chicken, cut into chunks. Mix lightly. Add seasoning to taste.
Place in baking dish. Spread cream of chicken soup over. Bake at 350°. Stir before serving.

title: sherried beef
directions: Put stew beef (or 7-bone roast) into a casserole.
Do not brown as it will brown during cooking.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours. Serve over rice.
Meat will be fork- tender and have a luscious brown gravy.
Great during the winter, especially during the busy holidays.

title: tabouli
directions: Combine bulgur wheat, hot water and salt together; let stand for 1/2 hour.
Cook until tender and let cool.
Mix all other ingredients in with bulgur mixture.
Chill for about 3 hours.

title: hawaiian charlie's corned beef hash patties
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and mash.
Add chopped onion and corned beef and mix all together.
Form into patties.
Fry for breakfast to accompany eggs.

title: oatmeal cookies(soft and chewy)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use ungreased cookie sheets.

title: bisquick dumplins
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Turn heat down to simmer.
Drop in dumplings by tablespoon.
Cook, uncovered, about 10 minutes. Cover and cook for another 10 minutes.

title: seven layer candy
directions: Put ingredients in order in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Blend sugar, cooking oil, flour, eggs and baking powder and mix well with an electric beater.
Spread 1/2 mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread apricot filling evenly over batter in pan.
Spread the balance of the batter over the filling.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may drizzle a sugar frosting or glaze over the top.
You may use any pie filling.

title: grandma stoner's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening/oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk alternately with flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix well. Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. If rolling and cutting cookies, use 8 cups flour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg thoroughly. Sift flour; blend all dry ingredients; stir into shortening mixture.
Chill dough.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve. Very good for get-togethers and parties.

title: kentucky burgoo
directions: Combine beef, soup bone, lamb, chicken, water, salt, pepper and red pepper in a very large, heavy pot with a tight fitting lid. Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 2 hours. Remove chicken from the soup, skin and bone; cut meat into bite-size pieces. Return chicken meat to pot. Add potatoes, onion, lima beans, carrots, green peppers and corn. Simmer 2 hours. Mixture will be thick but should not stick. Add water sparingly, if necessary, to keep from sticking. Add okra, tomatoes and garlic and simmer 1 1/2 hours longer. Add parsley and remove from stove.

title: sesame candy(pasteli)
directions: Blend sugar,
honey
and water in a pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring
frequently,
about
12 minutes or to soft ball (250° on candy thermometer).
Add sesame seed.
Spread on 8 x 8-inch buttered
pan, 3/4-inch thickness.	When cool, cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.

title: salted nut roll
directions: Melt margarine and chips at low heat.
Add milk; warm a little bit.
Stir in marshmallows.
Place 1/2 of peanuts in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread margarine mixture over peanuts and top with remaining nuts.
Press peanuts into mixture and chill.
Cut in squares.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix brown sugar, mustard and cornstarch over low heat.
Slowly stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes. Makes 2 cups sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions after chopping.
Place in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients well and pour on top of broccoli.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°, or until bubbly.
Do not cover.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter; cook to soft-ball stage. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips. Add Marshmallow Crme and vanilla. Add nuts. Beat well and pour in a greased pan or dish to cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage, drain and cool completely.
Shred cheese.
Add to sausage, then add Bisquick and water.
Mix with fork until blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15
minutes.
May be reheated in oven or microwave.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening until mixture resembles corn meal. Slowly add cold water until it makes dough. Roll dough out and cut into squares. In large pot; add milk, butter, salt and pepper to broth. Bring to a slow boil. Lower heat and simmer. Add dough one at a time, don't stir, and push down with a spoon. Add chicken slowly and cook for 15 minutes.

title: picadillo(pronounced picarea)
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients and add water, then simmer for fifteen or twenty minutes.
Saute together onions, green and red bell peppers, celery, Creole seasoning, cumin, garlic and Tabasco. Add meat, then add tomatoes, tomato sauce and Burgundy.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 or 20 minutes and serve over white rice.
Yum yum!!!

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Melt the chocolate in top of
double
boiler
with the 5 tablespoons water.	Cream the butter
and
sugar
well, add the egg yolks and whip.
Add
melted
chocolate,
slightly
cooled, the flour sifted with the baking powder and salt, and the milk. Fold in the stiffly whipped egg
whites and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x
2-inch
pan
and bake in moderate 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, egg yolks and lemon juice.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Mix well into a long baking dish.
Smash with a fork to cover the dish.
Bake at 350° until brown and let cool.

title: swedish meatballs from greta o'rourke
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beef, in blender.
Add to beef. Mix with hands and roll into balls.
Cook in oven at 425° for 3/4 hour.
Add 2 or 3 cans brown gravy*.
Cover with foil.
Cook additional 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan, 1/2 hotel pan.

title: easy berry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine well Bisquick, sugar and milk.
Pour mixture over butter in pan.
Pour in fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve topped with ice cream (Blue Bell makes a delicious fat-free vanilla).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: perfect pie meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with ice water and baking powder until stiff. Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk. Mix in dry ingredients and zucchini.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell and bake approximately 40 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine boiling water, shortening, sugar and salt. Allow to stand 3-4 minutes or until shortening is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Add the yeast mixture and eggs; mix well.
Add 2 c flour; beat until smooth.
Ad enough remaining flour to form a soft dough (do not knead).
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn dough onto a floured surface.
Pinch off a piece and form a 2 1/2 inch ball. Roll into a 5 inch rope and shape into a knot.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken delight
directions: Wash and season chicken to taste.
Place in greased casserole. If using rosemary, sprinkle over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 259° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Uncover and let bubble for few minutes.

title: cranberry-orange iced tea
directions: Add tea bags to boiling water.
Cover and steep 5 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Stir in sugar.
Let cool, then pour into large pitcher and add cranberry juice cocktail.
Pour over ice in tall glasses.
Garnish with orange slices.
Yield:
4 cups.
Fat:
0 grams.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, salt, soda and vanilla.
Add flour, uncooked quick oats, raisins and chopped nuts.
These may be rolled and sliced or dropped and formed in little balls to bake.
The dough may be frozen for baking at a later date.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peaches 'n crumb cake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add 2 tablespoons softened margarine and hot tap water to dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add egg and 1/2 cup flour. Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup flour to make a stiff batter.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick of butter in saucepan and set aside. In mixing bowl cream sugar and 1 stick of butter and add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk and soda, then fold in candy and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: dirt pie
directions: Make pudding and milk.
Put to side.
Mix cream cheese and butter with confectioners sugar.
Put to side.
Crush Oreos to powder.
Mix pudding mixture with cream cheese and butter mixture. Mix well.
Do one layer of cookies, one layer of pudding mixture, one layer of cookies, etc.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.
Decorate with flowers or gummy worms, etc.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Use microwave bacon rack; place paper towel and bacon.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes or until crispy.
Set aside.
Place frozen pie shell in quiche pan. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Press into shape of quiche pan. Brush with small amount Worcestershire sauce for color.
Prick with fork.
Microwave on 70% for 5 to 6 minutes or until light brown spots just begin to appear in crust.
Crumble bacon, cheese and onions in bottom of pie shell.

title: seafood mousse
directions: Heat soup.
Blend in cream cheese. Dissolve gelatine in cold water and add to soup mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend and chill for 8 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together over low heat.
Stir until boiling.
Serve with chips.

title: country chicken chowder
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add chicken; cook until browned.
Add cooked chicken, onions, celery, carrots, corn, soup, chicken broth and dill to slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours, or until chicken is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Turn off heat; stir in half and half.
Cover and let stand 5 to 10 minutes or just until heated through.
May garnish with croutons and fresh dill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: healthy carrot bread
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together.
Blend next 5 ingredients in order given.
Stir all together easily with minimum strokes. Turn into an oiled and floured baking ring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until it is mixed well.
Makes 1 quart.

title: tomato soup
directions: Return to stove and cook until thick.
Pour in jars and process 5 minutes.

title: creole chicken and rice
directions: Combine 3/4 cup of water and salt in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in rice.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed; keep warm.

title: easy pierogi
directions: Cook lasagna noodles following package directions.
Set aside. Peel and boil potatoes.
Mash until smooth.
Combine mashed potatoes with cheese, 1/4 melted butter or margarine and parsley. Beat until fluffy.

title: black boston cupcakes
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and add the egg and chocolate chips. Set aside.
Mix together the flour, cocoa, sugar and salt; set aside.
Mix together the water, oil, vinegar and vanilla and add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Fill paper cups 1/3 full of batter. Top each with a heaping teaspoonful of the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle top with sugar and chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, eggs, oil and yeast together.
Let stand in a warm place while preparing apple mix.
Chop apples into small pieces.
Put into another bowl; add sugar and cinnamon.
Stir. Then add apple mix to pancake mix.
Heat griddle to 350°; melt margarine.
Then when ready, place mix on forming pancakes.
Brown both sides.
Serve with favorite syrup or jam.
Makes 12 to 13 pancakes.

title: mouse ears
directions: Heat the milk, sugar, salt and shortening, but do not boil. Cool this until it is room temperature and add yeast until dissolved.
Mix the flour into mixture and let rise for 30 minutes. Pinch off small pieces and stretch until very thin.
Fry this on each side and place on toweling to drain.
Sprinkle the ears with powdered sugar or cinnamon sugar.
Make plenty of these when the kids come home from school.
They disappear like magic.

title: molasses cookie
directions: Mix ingredients with enough flour to make a roll. Let stand overnight. Slice and bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook over medium heat sugar, cornstarch, milk and egg until thickened.
Add peanut butter and oleo.
Mix well; pour into baking shell.
Cool and cover with Cool Whip.

title: ground chuck rice and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, bell pepper and celery and drain off liquid. Add all other ingredients (except cheese).
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Cook in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: white sauce(food processor)
directions: Heat milk, but do not bring to boiling point.
Place steel cutting blade into mixing container.
Process butter, flour and seasonings until well mixed.
Continue processing while slowly adding hot milk through feeder tube.
When thoroughly blended, pour mixture into saucepan and cook over medium heat until thickened.

title: easy lentil salad
directions: In a heavy 2 to 3-quart sauce, bring 1-quart of water and 1 teaspoon of the salt to a boil over high heat.
Drop in lentils, reduce the heat to low and simmer partially covered for 20 to 30 minutes, or until the lentils are tender but still intact.
Drain them in a sieve or colander; spread them on a double thickness of paper towels and pat them completely dry.
Transfer the lentils to a large serving bowl and stir in the chopped onions, scallions, 2 tablespoons of parsley and the garlic.

title: chicago cake
directions: Mix together and put in greased tube pan and cook for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, cut and layer ingredients.
Begin with lettuce, red onion, celery, green pepper and green peas.
Seal with mayonnaise and sprinkle with sugar.
Add Cheddar cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill and shape.
Bread and fry croquettes in deep pot.
Drain on towels before serving.
Makes 12 croquettes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Make the popcorn, then melt butter in deep nonstick saucepan. Add 2 cups of brown sugar and corn syrup.
Boil for 5 minutes, then add baking soda and vanilla.
Put popcorn and liquid mixture in a deep dish pan.
Then put in oven for one hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes or until done.

title: lemon lust
directions: Make jello with 3 1/2 cups hot water and can of lemonade. Refrigerate for 30 minutes, until cooled, but not jelled.
Mix in Cool Whip (no pieces) and pour into large Tupperware mold or bowl. Refrigerate.
Make 1 day in advance.

title: highbush cranberry catsup
directions: Boil together until soft the onions, cranberries and water. Rub through a sieve; discard seeds.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Boil until thick.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate in pan.
Add sugar and milk and stir constantly until mixture starts to boil.
Take off stove and add butter and vanilla.
Beat with egg beater until smooth.
(This will keep in refrigerator for weeks, if it lasts that long.)

title: russian tea cakes(cookies)
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and mix in flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Make into balls.
Bake at 400° until brown (about 15 minutes), then roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs alternately with milk and dry ingredients.
Stir in fruit and nuts; drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Makes approximately 16 dozen.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, egg, oatmeal or cracker crumbs, salt and
pepper
together.
Put
mixture into a 9-inch round pan. Smash
down
to
make
a
crust form.
Bake meat mixture (crust) for
15 to 20 minutes, or until done, in a 350° oven. Mix
to 6
servings of instant potatoes.
When crust (meat mixture)
is done, spread mashed potatoes over top, then slice cheese and put over potatoes.
Put back in oven until brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together. Blend into sugar mixture.
Fold in carrots.
Bake 1 hour in a greased 13 x 8-inch pan at 300°.

title: chicken rotini stir-fry
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken, broccoli, carrots and onion.
Cook and stir over medium heat until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Add water, bouillon and tarragon.
Cook and stir until chicken is cooked through.
Add hot, cooked rotini and Parmesan cheese; toss to coat.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: red magic meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Form into a loaf (8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inch) pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place the 8 pieces of chicken in a baking dish.
Refrigerate while preparing sauce.
Combine all other ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over the chicken and cover. Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
Bake in a preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.
Check chicken for doneness.

title: omelet of potatoes and eggs(tortilla espanola)
directions: Pre-soak a clay pot, top and bottom, in water for 15 minutes. Saute the onions, mushrooms, green pepper and garlic in the olive oil until the onions turn golden brown, then remove from the oil and set aside.
In the same frying pan, brown the chicken parts on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and set aside, then brown the cut-up sausage and set aside.

title: piggie brownies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk; set aside.
Mix cake mix and 1 1/3 cups evaporated milk, stirring until it holds together.
Put half the cake mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for about 6 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in a shallow pan of water and bake at 400° for about 45 minutes or until thick and browned.
Stir once before it thickens.
Serves 6.

title: chicken encharito
directions: Stew and debone chicken; save broth for gravy.
Bring broth to boil.
Add green chillies; thicken with flour.
Remove from heat. Add sour cream.
Layer in casserole pan the diced chicken, onion, cheese, cut up tortillas and gravy.
Top with last of gravy and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar with cocoa, then add milk and butter. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, oats, and vanilla. Spoon out onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together shortening and brown sugar.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla to cream mixture.
Mix well. Mix in dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: select deli salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to directions.
In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients (except dressing); toss to mix, then add just enough Italian dressing to make moist.
Chill thoroughly. Toss gently before serving.

title: best bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin pan with 12 paper baking cups.
Combine bran and skim milk.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add all at once to bran mixture, stirring just to mix.
Mix oil, brown sugar, egg whites and molasses thoroughly.
Blend into bran mixture.
Stir in raisins and dates.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Remove papers.
Muffins can be frozen at this point.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cucumbers should be fresh and washed thoroughly.
Do not peel. Slice cucumbers and onions very thinly in a large pan.
Mix with salt and vinegar and let stand at least 3 hours.
Drain, nearly dry.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Place over low heat to simmer point.
Do not allow to boil.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven
to
Melt
margarine
in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix
sugar and water together.
Set aside.
Make dough of
flour,
Crisco
and
milk.
Roll out to a rectangle. Mix 2
cups chopped apples and cinnamon together.
Spread over dough. Roll up the jelly roll fashion.
Slice into 16 slices. Lay	rolls in	melted	margarine.
Carefully pour sugar/water mixture over rolls.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.

title: delicious ham mousse
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: french toast(low-fat)
directions: Spray pan with Pam and dip bread into Egg Beaters.
Fry until golden brown. Turn and fry second side.
Put cinnamon and sugar on finished toast and pour on syrup.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cornstarch, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat the butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Press chocolate kiss, flat side down, into each ball and then press dough up sides of kiss until only point is visible.
Bake until light brown at the edge and beginning to brown on top, about 10 minutes.

title: tramp soup
directions: Put together in pan with a little water and salt. Cook until well done. Add milk; bring to a boil. Serve with crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and cook meat as directed on taco seasoning mix.
On large serving dish, layer tortilla chips, cooked meat, shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, 1/2 jar salsa and cheese.
Top with olives.
Serve with remaining salsa and sour cream on side. Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Bake chicken until done.
Remove meat from bones.

title: glazed pork and rice dinner
directions: Cook chops in non-stick skillet until browned.
Remove chops. Add broth, preserves and mustard.
Heat to a boil.
Stir in rice. Top with chops.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.

title: easy cake cookies
directions: Mix ingredients by hand until moistened.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool and frost.
(We like Funfetti mix because it makes them look neat.)

title: corn pea salad
directions: Pour first 3 ingredients cooled over all the rest.
Marinate a day or more, at least overnight, stirring occasionally.
Remove from marinade when serving.

title: country style steak
directions: Dredge steak in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
After it is browned on both sides, remove from pan and add 1 tablespoon flour to the drippings in pan.
Slowly stir in water to form a gravy.
Add onion flakes.
Return the meat to the skillet and cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: hershey's one bowl syrup cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar and eggs until thoroughly blended. Add flour and baking soda, blending well.
Add syrup; mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Frost as desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sour cream corn casserole
directions: Bring corn to a boil; drain and set aside.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Fry onion in bacon drippings; add flour and sour cream. Pour corn and rest of mixture in casserole.
Add milk for consistency.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: doonan's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Shape into oval loaf; place in suitable pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: With meat mallet pound each chicken breast half between two sheets of plastic wrap to 1/2-inch thickness.
In flat bowl, beat eggs, slightly; place bread crumbs in pie plate.
Dip chicken pieces into eggs, then into bread crumbs to coat evenly.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Mix margarine, cheese and vanilla in a large glass bowl. Microwave 3 minutes on High power.
Stir.
Add the cocoa and stir. Add the powdered sugar and stir.
Microwave 1 minute on High power and stir.
Add the pecans and stir.
Mixture will be thick. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch flat pan sprayed with Pam.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Cool.
Add Seven-Up, marshmallows and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: orange pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ice cream container. Fill the remainder with regular milk, leaving 2-inches of space at top.
Mix and freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturers directions.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on.
Peel and slice 1/4-inch thick crosswise.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Place potato slices in buttered dish.
Cover with combined ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Cut bananas, put on top of creamed ingredients.
Drain pineapple.
Put on top of bananas.
Top with Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
This is just one of my favorite recipes so feel free to call me when it's

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt margarine and Cheez Whiz together.
Drain Veg-All; mix together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and put on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to a wire rack.
Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: eggplant-crab meat casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in water to cover for about 20 minutes.
Drain and mash.
In large mixing bowl, combine eggplant with minced onion, one cup bread crumbs, one cup cheese, salt, pepper and butter; mix thoroughly.
Add crab meat and beaten eggs.

title: pasta carbonara(for 10 people)
directions: Cut bacon into 4 pieces.
Cook until done, but not crispy; drain.
Chop onion into 1-inch pieces and saute in butter until lightly golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Clean and quarter mushrooms.
Clean parsley.

title: brisket in natural gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place brisket, together with onions, carrots, bay leaves, garlic, salt and pepper in Dutch oven or heavy roasting pan with tightly fitting cover.
Add enough water to just cover meat.
Cover tightly and cook in preheated oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until brisket is fork-tender.
Remove brisket to platter.

title: boston mud pie
directions: Layer 1:
Mix together nuts, flour and margarine.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 pie tins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin; dissolve completely.
Do not add cold water!
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 3 hours.

title: banana whip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Pour dissolved gelatin in blender and add lemon juice and sugar and mix one minute.
Add egg whites and vanilla and mix.
Gradually add banana while blending. Remove mixture to large bowl and add cherries.
Pour into a mold and chill.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and salt together. Add flour and whipping cream alternately to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Start in a cold oven, turning on at 325° when you place cake in oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian sausage bites
directions: Cut each sausage link into 10 slices.
Remove casing and place in a nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Cook 4 minutes or until well browned, turning once.
Remove from skillet; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine diced tomatoes, sauce mix, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Add sausage, stirring to combine.
Place in a chafing dish or slow cooker.
Serve with wooden party picks. Yield: 10 to 15 servings.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, water and eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread chips over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: granola cookies
directions: Beat together the margarine and brown sugar; blend in egg, milk and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix together the cereal, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add the cereal mixture to the butter mixture; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool for about 1 minute on the sheet before removing to cooling rack.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of sugar over yeast and water.
Let stand 5 minutes while warming. When cooled add milk, 1/4 cup margarine, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and beaten egg.
Gradually add flour.
Add enough flour to make soft dough and knead until smooth.
Turn into buttered bowl and let rise until double.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: oat-tofu burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 8 large patties. Brown slowly on both sides, allowing patties to cook well in a nonstick pan which has been prepared by rubbing a few drops of olive oil over the cooking surface.
Serves 3.

title: chocolate town special cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pan.
Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Make a paste of cocoa and water.
Cool slightly.
Add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Layer 1:
Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into an 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, the yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat all liquids until warm.
Add to dry mix; beat well.
Stir in the rest of flour real well.
Grease pan with Crisco.
Put corn meal in pans.
Put in the dough.
Cover and let rise 1 time.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.
Cool on rack. Yields 2 loaves.

title: broccoli bake casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, blend together soup and cheese.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Carefully stir in broccoli and top with melted oleo.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease or spray pan.
Spread pecans over bottom of pan.
Do the same for coconut.
Make the cake mix using directions on box and then pour over the coconut.
Melt the butter and cream cheese. Stir occasionally. When melted, mix with sugar.
Pour mix over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done (time may vary).

title: lumpia
directions: In a bowl, combine pork, shrimp, water chestnuts, mushrooms, onion, salt, pepper and egg.
At one end of the lumpia wrapper, spoon about 2 tablespoons of the pork mixture and roll tightly. Brush end of the wrapper with water to seal it.
Deep fry.
When slightly cool, cut into 2-inch pieces.
Serve hot with sweet-sour sauce or hot Thai sauce which can be bought at most Filipino store or Oriental stores in Moreno Valley.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together; roll into balls.
Brown in skillet in small amount of grease.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce and water; top with catsup.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple until bubbly. Add Jell-O and sugar.
Dissolve. Cool. Add buttermilk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate.

title: secret kisses
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and vanilla together.
Blend together the flour and pecans with the creamed ingredients and chill.
Roll 1 teaspoon of dough around a Kiss.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool well.
Roll in sifted confectioners sugar. Bake at 300° to 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Boil rice until tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Drain.
Mix with a spoon. Add cream of chicken soup, Cheez Whiz and broccoli. Put in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Sprinkle croutons on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cooked applesauce cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake 35-40 minutes or till done.

title: chicken long rice
directions: Boil chicken pieces (to make broth).
Set broth aside.
Skin and debone chicken.
Cut into pieces.
Heat oil in skillet; saute chicken and garlic until brown.
Add broth, ginger and salt. Simmer 1 hour.
Soak long rice for 30 minutes.
Add to chicken. Sprinkle with green onions.
Serves 6.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass or metal baking dish.
Heat sugar and water in medium saucepan until sugar dissolves; set aside.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth. Knead gently just until smooth.
Roll out to a 12 x 10 x 1/4-inch rectangle.
Stir together apples and cinnamon in mixing bowl. Sprinkle apples evenly over dough.
Roll up jelly-roll style, beginning with a long side.
Press edges to seal.
Cut into 16 slices, each about 1/2-inch thick.

title: chicken and dressing in layers
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Toss lightly. Place alternate layers of chicken and dressing in a greased 9 x
13-inch pan ending with dressing.
Pour broth from cooking chicken over all, until it can be seen around edges.
Bake for 1
hour
Cover with foil at start.
Uncover to brown slightly.
Cut in squares and serve.
Serves 12.

title: soft molasses drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine molasses and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in flour.
Add raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° about 8 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix together thoroughly grated cheese, sausage, and Bisquick. Mixture will be very stiff and should be kneaded well.
Set aside. Slit and seed the peppers.
If you prefer mild peppers, rinse seeded peppers under running water thoroughly.
Stuff each pepper with a sliver of cheese.
Pinch the pepper closed around the cheese.

title: ham n eggs brunch braid
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place cream cheese and milk in bowl. Microwave on high 1 minute.
Whisk until smooth.
Add eggs, salt and pepper, whisk to combine.
Chop bell pepper and add pepper and onion to egg mixture.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add egg mixture; cook stirring occasionally, until eggs are set but still moist.
Remove from heat.

title: aunt babe's pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until pecans rise to the top.

title: beauty queen shortcut shortcake
directions: Open the angel food cake and place on cake plate. Cover cake with Cool Whip. Fill the hole in the center of the cake with berries. Add any decorative touches on top of cake with the berries you choose. Any left over berries should be placed next to the finished cake for those who might like extra berries with their serving.

title: easy dump cake
directions: Do not drain pineapple!
Mix pineapple and fruit filling. Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover with dry cake mix.
Top with nuts and melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: unrolled cabbage rolls
directions: Layer in casserole:
thin sliced cabbage, 1/2 ground beef/onion mixture, 1/2 can tomato soup, 2 or 3 handfuls long grain rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat layers.
Add 1 soup can of water. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350° or all day in a crock-pot.

title: lime and lemon punch(very pretty)
directions: Combine the Seven-Up and lemonade; add lime sherbet at last to suit your taste.
Stir until foamy.
Throw in a few ice cubes.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Cut steak into cubes.
Put in casserole dish.
Put soups and water over meat.
Stir.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove cover last 15 to 20 minutes for sauce to thicken.

title: hungarian butter cookies
directions: Work together flour, yolks, butter and yeast.
Add and knead cream and salt.
Put dough in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out dough in 10x sugar.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares and fill with whatever.
Overlap dough.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.

title: gee-cheezy whizzy
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop from spoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: roast pork tenderloin
directions: Mix marinade ingredients together.
Brush or soak tenderloins several hours (or overnight) before cooking and also during cooking.
Roast, uncovered, in a 300° oven until tender, 1 3/4 to 2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion and green pepper together and pour 1 cup of sugar on top.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs; drain.
Combine reserved pineapple liquid, lemon juice, sugar, soy sauce and ginger.
In a small cup, stir 1 teaspoon of mixture into cornstarch; set aside.
Add remaining mixture to skillet.
Cover, simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add pineapple and green pepper; heat.
Gradually stir in cornstarch mixture.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: fish court bouillon
directions: Cut fillets into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Marinate in wine mixed with liquid smoke for 1 to 2 hours.
In oleo, saute onions, celery, bell pepper, garlic, and green onions.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Add fish, marinade and parsley.
Cook covered about 40 to 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook longer to reduce liquid if necessary. Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 10.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with pie crust, homemade or canned biscuits.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together, drop cookies onto greased sheet.	Bake at 350 degrees.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save syrup).
Add water to make 1 cup.
Heat to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Let cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partially set.
Blend fruits; fold gelatin into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill firm.
Prepare topping according to package.
Blend in cheese.
Spread over gelatin. Toast nuts in 1 tablespoon butter at 350° for 10 minutes. Sprinkle on top.
Chill.
Serves 9.

title: pink lassies
directions: Place all ingredients in blender. Cover and blend until smooth 25 to 30 seconds.

title: fancy chicken
directions: Place 8 slices of dried beef in bottom of a slightly greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each breast piece and roll up.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place on beef.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream and soup; pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until done.

title: mexican corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread as directed.
Cool and crumble, then add rest of ingredients.

title: onion pie(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Note:
Use Vidalia or Texas Sweet onions if possible.

title: chicken-n-rice casserole
directions: Lay chicken pieces in a Dutch oven or large deep bowl suitable for baking.
Pour rice over chicken pieces.

title: tangy vegetable dip
directions: Makes 3 cups dip.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot clam dip
directions: In top of double boiler, melt butter.
Add onion and green pepper.
Put over direct heat and saute 3 minutes.
Put back on double boiler.
Add minced clams, cheese, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, sherry and red pepper.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring all the time.

title: pickled mostaccioli
directions: Cook pasta as directed, adding food coloring to water.
Drain; toss with a small amount of oil to prevent sticking.
