Place remaining ingredients in a blender.
Blend and pour over mostaccioli.
Refrigerate.
Better when it sits a day.
Will keep 4 weeks.

title: hungarian veal and peppers
directions: Spray nonstick pan with cooking spray.
Brown meat cubes over moderate heat; turn to brown evenly.
Stir in 2 tablespoons water and onion.
Cook and stir until water evaporates and onion begins to brown.
Watch carefully.
Stir in chicken broth and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes.
Uncover and simmer until most of liquid evaporates.
Serve with cooked noodles or rice.

title: heath bar candy
directions: Melt the butter in pan. Pour in the brown sugar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes. Place the crackers side by side in a cookie pan (make sure it has edges). Pour the mixture over the crackers. Heat in oven at 400° for 10 minutes (maybe less; watch so they don't burn). Take out and add the chocolate chips on top. Wait a few minutes and spread chocolate all over. Place in freezer for 1 hour. Take out; cut with pizza cutter and serve. Keep leftovers refrigerated.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornmeal and flour.
Beat egg yolks with milk.
Add creamed butter into sugar and milk mixture, beating well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 315°.
Bake for another 30 minutes or until set.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut vegetables in bite-size pieces and toss lightly.
Combine dressing ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: southwestern pork stew
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Cut pork into 3/4-inch cubes. Combine next 4 ingredients in a large Ziploc bag.
Add pork and shake to coat.
Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add pork and cook 5 minutes. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute 3 minutes. Stir in potato and next 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in corn.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes.
Ladle stew into bowls and garnish with cilantro.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, flour and sugar; beat well.
Add milk, corn and salt; stir together well.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Add corn mixture to butter in baking dish; stir well.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes or until firm.
Stir mixture well halfway through baking time.
Makes 10 servings.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 15 minutes; then add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer for 5 minutes over heat.
Strain.
It makes 4 quarts.

title: divinity
directions: Combine ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring only until sugar dissolves (soft ball stage).
In a bowl, beat 2 egg whites stiff and pour 1/2 of the cooked syrup mixture over while beating. Keep stirring egg whites and syrup mixture while cooking remainder of syrup to hard ball stage.
Pour hard ball syrup over egg white mixture and add vanilla.
Keep beating until stiff; add chopped nuts, if desired.
Beat mixture until thick.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper to cool.
If stored in layers, put wax paper between layers.

title: jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello and
strawberries
in hot water well and put in refrigerator
until
it begins to congeal.
Mix 3/4 of Cool Whip into jello (fold).	Tear cake into mixture; mix and pour into long pan.
Let stand 24 hours. Top with remainder of Cool Whip.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in two 9-inch round cake pans in moderate oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar or caramel icing.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients in blender, beginning with liquids and adding squash last.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: delicious christmas salad
directions: Pour 1 cup hot water over raspberry Jell-O; stir for 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and chill until set, but not firm.
Fold in oranges, pineapple, cranberry sauce and walnuts. Chill until firm.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Shape meatballs and place singularly in flat pan.

title: deep dish crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 425°.
Combine milk, eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add crabmeat, grated cheeses and spinach to milk mixture; blend in blender or mixer.
Add flour or Bisquick. Pour into pie shell.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves six.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Place apples in mixing bowl.
Add sugar and let stand for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla; blend together.
Mix and sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Add walnuts.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan until done.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Saute steak in oil until browned.
Add all other ingredients (except vegetables) and cook until tender.
Add vegetables and simmer until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: baked green beans
directions: Fry bacon and break into pieces.
Chop onion and brown in bacon grease.
Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: bean and beef stew
directions: Brown beef in a large skillet. Drain off fat.
Add chopped onion and green pepper. Cook until soft. Add kidney beans (undrained), tomatoes and corn. Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer slowly until slightly thickened.
Serve in bowls with all the delicious juices.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in slices and brown in oil for 10 to 15 minutes. Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water and add to meat. Cover and simmer 25 minutes. Add tomatoes and bell pepper and simmer 15 minutes more. Mix flour and water and add to soy sauce. Add to meat and stir until thickened. Cook 30 minutes more. Serve over hot cooked rice or noodles.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals.
Uncover and cook to hard ball stage (258°).
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites in large bowl until foamy.
Add Jell-O and beat until stiff peaks form. Pour hot syrup in egg whites while beating and beat on high 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts and drop on wax paper by teaspoon.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: tara's blue ribbon sour cream pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and lightly flour 12-cup fluted tube pan.
In large bowl, cream together sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and orange peel.
Add alternately with sour cream, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Invert onto a serving plate.
Serves 16.

title: famous lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Gradually add boiling water.
Boil gently 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: bubbly bessie's passover brisket
directions: In a deep roasting pan (layered with aluminum foil to keep juices in) place brisket.
Slice 2 good sized onions, 3 cloves of garlic, 1 pound mushrooms and 2 bay leaves.
Cover brisket with a small jar of kosher apricot preserves and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Add 1 1/2 cups ginger ale or selzer and cook at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour in pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: pul ko-kee
directions: Slice meat in thin strips across the grain.
Add all other ingredients and marinate at least 1 hour.
Brown in pan on top of stove, or grill over charcoal.
Serve with plain rice.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Brown meat and cook onions until tender.
Stir to separate meat; drain off fat.
Add soups, water, potatoes, beans, carrots, celery, salt and pepper.
Place in 2-quart shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well or sift until no streaks are left.
Store in airtight container.

title: scalloped franks 'n' corn
directions: Cut hot dogs into quarters.
Combine corn and milk in saucepan; heat through.
Remove from heat.
Stir a little of corn mixture into eggs; gradually stir eggs into corn mixture.
Add cracker crumbs, green pepper, onion, sugar and pepper.
Stir in half of hot dogs; pour mixture into greased 2-quart casserole. Place rest of hot dogs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: punch for a party
directions: Melt citric acid in 1/4 cup hot water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
This may be made ahead of time.
There's nothing to add at the last minute.

title: virginia's chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate on double boiler.
Add sugar and butter. Remove from heat and add egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks.
Add flour to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Combine 1/3 egg white mixture with chocolate mixture. Mix well.
Fold in remaining egg white.
Pour into 8-inch spring-form, well buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with unsweetened cream.

title: low calorie strawberry pie(sugarless)
directions: Mix pudding mix, gelatin and water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add orange concentrate.
Let mixture cool and fold in Cool Whip.
Put in baked pie crust and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Makes 6 or 8 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes slightly.
Melt 1/4 cup oleo and mix with potatoes.
Mix all ingredients (except corn flakes and remaining 1/4 cup oleo) and put into a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Top with melted oleo and corn flake mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, pineapple and mandarin oranges. Add dry Jell-O and mix well; fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss together.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream together 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Add pretzels and press into 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and add frozen berries.
Stir and let partially set up.
Cream cheese and sugar together well.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over pretzel mixture. Pour jello mixture over cream cheese layer and refrigerate.

title: sloppy joes(serves 4 to 6)
directions: In skillet brown meat with onions and pepper.
Drain off fat. Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Add all other ingredients (except buns) and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on heated buns.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in salted water until tender. Drain well. Mix in the rest of the ingredients. Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sugar plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a generously greased 10-inch Bundt pan, coated with sugar (generously).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan. Serves 12.

title: easy mexican cheese dip
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, cube Velveeta.
Pour salsa over cubes. Mix.
Microwave for 9 minutes on High, stirring every 3 minutes. Serve hot with chips, pretzels or veggies.

title: conch chowder
directions: Clean and prepare
conch.
Dice in small pieces.
Place in pot and
boil
until
tender.
Season with salt and pepper. Add celery and bell pepper.

title: "mom's" sugar cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Put in an unbaked pie shell; sprinkle with butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.

title: salad
directions: Mix eggs, flour, sugar, mustard and juice from pineapple chunks.
Cook in double boiler.
Cool.
Add 2 cups of marshmallows.
Add fruit.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and add shrimp.
Refrigerate for a few hours.
Serve at room temperature with party size bread or crackers.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Smash together all ingredients except cheese.
Layer meat mixture, layer Mozzarella cheese and layer of meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. When almost done baking, put on top layer of Mozzarella cheese.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and peanut butter together with salt.
Add sugars.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well. Gradually add in flour and soda.
Mix until well blended.
At this point, stir in chips or nuts with a wooden spoon.
Roll into balls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter and press with fork on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown hamburger, then drain.
Mix cheese, onion and Ro-Tel in microwave 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
This may be heated in saucepan on top of stove on low heat.
Mix hamburger with cheese mixture and serve with chips of your choice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with undrained pineapple.
Add marshmallows and chopped nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix and put in 8 x 8-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.

title: polo a lo miami(spanish for chicken a la miami)
directions: Cut chicken into eight pieces.
Mix egg, milk, flour, salt and pimiento together and beat.
Dip chicken pieces into mixture and fry in oil approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: pecan pie(makes two large pies.)
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites until stiff.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, melted oleo, syrup, vanilla and nutmeg.
Fold in egg whites and mix well.
Put pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mash peaches with sugar and lemon juice in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Stir in creams; transfer to ice cream maker and freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Makes 6 cups.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Mix together salt, oil and milk.
Mix with fork all dry ingredients until moistened.
Press in pie plate and flute edges.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.
Can be reheated.
Can be frozen.

title: wedding punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Add pineapple juice, lemonade, water and extracts.
Mix early in the day and let stand until 1 hour before serving.
Add large pieces of ice to chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serves approximately 35 to 40.

title: mary's egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake in 350° preheated oven.

title: six-cup fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and allow to stand in refrigerator for several hours (overnight is better) before serving.

title: crock-pot boston baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine egg product, evaporated milk, salt and black pepper in large bowl. Add potatoes, cheese, onion, bell pepper and ham; mix well. Pour mixture into prepared baking dish. Bake for 60 to 65 minutes or until set.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add pecans and flour.
Roll into balls with your hands and barely flatten on cookie sheet.
If cookie dough has been refrigerated, it is easier to work into balls.
Bake at 300° about 45 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Store in cookie tin.

title: strawberry creme
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in saucepan to soften.
Wash strawberries and remove stems.
Reserve a few berries for garnish. Assemble and attach fruit/vegetable strainer.
Turn to speed 4 and strain strawberries in bowl.
Attach bowl and flat beater. Add 1 cup cream, sugar and salt to strawberry puree.
Turn to stir speed and beat until well blended.

title: chicken soup
directions: Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic in butter.
Stir in flour and brown.
Add broth and stir.
Add chicken and salt and pepper to taste.
Add parsley flakes to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over Uncle Ben's wild rice with seasoning or regular rice.

title: hearty hodgepodge soup
directions: Saute onions, celery and garlic in margarine (about 2 tablespoons) until tender.
Add ground beef and cook until gray; stir in soup, beans and other ingredients.
Add 3 cups of water. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shells florentine
directions: In a nonstick skillet over medium heat, cook mushrooms, onion, garlic, Italian seasoning and pepper in liquid Butter Buds until tender, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, spinach and Egg Beaters.
Spoon into cooked shells.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass casserole dish that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Arrange shells in sauce and a layer of grated cheese.
Pour the rest of the sauce over shells and top with remaining grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
Set aside.
Drain juice off fruit; set aside.
Pour juice in saucepan; add sugar, flour, eggs and salt.
Cook on stove, stirring constantly on low heat; bring to a boil.
Let sit a minute before adding macaroni, Cool Whip and fruit.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: chocolate caramel bars or turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Put 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Melt together in top of double boiler. Spread melted mixture on top of baked cake, then pour other half of cake batter over the top and return to oven; bake 15 minutes at 350° or longer, until done.

title: mocha crisps
directions: Blend butter, coffee, salt, almonds, extract and vanilla. Beat in sugar.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Add chips.
Spread in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes; break into pieces.

title: tuna treats
directions: Mix together and press into 6 buttered muffin tins.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup grated cheese. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until well blended.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: turkey dish
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth and remove from heat.
Combine salad dressing, turkey, cooked noodles, peas, pepper and oregano. Stir in onion mixture. Pour into shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Garnish top with tomato wedges, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Brown celery and onion separately. Combine all ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours, covered, in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles over for the last 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut and pork chop casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in a large casserole.
Add 2 cups of water. Sprinkle in sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Add chopped pepper and sliced onion.
Place pork chops on top (seasoned to taste).
Bake in 350° oven with a cover until pork chops are tender.

title: nut crackers sweets
directions: Make 12 cracker "sandwiches" with peanut butter filling.
In 2-quart casserole, place chocolate and shortening.
Microwave on "5" for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes until melted.
Drizzle over peanut butter layer. With knife or small spatula, swirl mixtures. Refrigerate until firm. Break in pieces.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir all ingredients except flour, then stir flour in a little at a time. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 for 10 minutes.

title: fresh shrimp salad
directions: Place shrimp and water in 12 cup casserole. Cover and microwave 4 minutes.
Remove casserole from microwave and let stand 2 minutes on counter, covered.
Drain shrimp and cool under cold running water.
Drain well.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Make large cookie on pizza pan, reasonably thick.
Cook until soft and barely tan.
Mix powdered sugar with whipped cream cheese.
Spread on warm cookie.
Mix orange juice with cornstarch. Cook on low heat until clear for glaze.
Arrange fresh fruits on top of cookie and cream cheese.
Pour on glaze while warm. Arrange outside to center.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Cook and cool bacon, then crumble.
Mix celery, green onions, peanuts and bacon.
Just before serving, add frozen peas and gently mix with sour cream.

title: green bean rolls
directions: Cut bacon strips in half. Secure 9 to 10 beans, stacked into bundle, with toothpicks. Place bundles in 9 x 13 pan. Combine all other ingredients and pour over beans. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pansy apple cake
directions: Mix the sugar, apples, and cinnamon and set aside.
Mix in order listed the remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and line the bottom of a tube pan with waxed paper.
Layer with batter and apple mixture ending with batter.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: wassail punch
directions: Boil cider, cloves and rind for six minutes.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Serve hot.

title: monster toast
directions: Pour 4 separate cups of milk.
Add a different color food coloring to each cup.
Paint a face on a piece of bread, using the food coloring "paint".
Toast the bread.
Butter lightly.
Eat!

title: heath bar cake
directions: Stir sugar into flour and mix well.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture is like cornmeal.
Measure out 1 cup and set aside.
To the rest of mixture, add egg, milk, soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with topping and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bourbon-glazed beef or pork ribs
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Arrange ribs on broiling pan lined with foil.
Combine remaining ingredients for glaze.
Brush ribs with a thin coat of glaze and place in oven.
Brush frequently and generously for 1 hour.
Ribs will be medium cooked.
Continue cooking and basting for well cooked ribs.

title: beef cube casserole
directions: Put all ingredients together in a roaster.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for approximately 3 hours.
Put over rice or noodles.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Spread pretzels on cookie sheet.
Mix remaining ingredients; drizzle over pretzels and mix.
Bake at 200° for 45 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini beef bake
directions: Wash and cut ends off squash; cut in 1/2-inch slices. Cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes or until tender; drain. In skillet, cook meat with onion; drain off fat. Stir in bread crumbs and thyme. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: community cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together in large bowl: sugar, butter, cream cheese, vanilla and egg yolks.
Mix flour a little at
a time.
Cover bowl and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Separate out a portion of dough.
Put the rest back in the refrigerator.
On a floured board, roll out the dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Using cookie cutters, cut out the shapes and place on a cookie sheet.
Before baking, brush top of cookies with egg whites or decorate baked cookies with Fun Frosting and sprinkles. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cookies are done when light brown.
Remove cookies and place them on a wire rack for cooling. Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: portuguese spiced enchiladas and beans
directions: Cook beans 1 hour before adding spices.
Melt shortening, 1/2 teaspoon allspice, 1/2 teaspoon cumin, 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon chili powder, garlic and salt and cook until beans are tender.
Brown ground beef, add 1 teaspoon allspice, 1 teaspoon cumin and garlic salt and simmer 10 minutes.
Melt 3 tablespoons shortening.
Add flour, garlic salt, sauce and 1 1/2 to 2 cans water.
Cook until thickened like gravy.
Using 1/2 the sauce, dip tortillas in sauce.
Place 2 tablespoons meat, top with onion, 3 olives and cheese.
Fold tortillas and place in baking dish. Repeat for 12 tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and pour remaining sauce over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with beans.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together, then cut out center of a loaf of rye bread and fill with mixture.

title: peppers and onion rings(to can)
directions: Wash peppers; remove seeds and slice.
Wash again and measure. Mix with the onion slices and add other ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Bring to a good boil; stir and can in sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: nuclear omelette
directions: In a bowl, mix eggs and milk.
Add lemon pepper.
In nonstick skillet over medium heat, melt 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine. Add eggs and cover.
Let cook slowly.
Before eggs are set up completely, add spices to taste (be careful).
As eggs are totally set up, flip over to brown.
Add cheese, chili, meat and vegetables; flip half over to cover.
Let cook until ingredients are warm and cheese is melted.
Serve with hash brown potatoes, toast and juice.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Soak in large bowl of salted water for 5 to 30 minutes.
Dry between paper towels.
Fry slices in small amount of hot oil.
Remove and salt to taste.
Chop tomato and sprinkle on top of slices.
Top with yogurt.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crust for fruit squares
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients with fork until crumbly.
Add the egg yolk, beaten with milk to total 3/4 cup.
Mix and lightly knead, then roll.
Use over 1/2 of dough for the bottom and the remaining for the top.

title: peach cheese delight
directions: Drain peaches and pineapple, reserving juices.
Combine juices and water, if necessary, to make 2 cups of liquid.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add 1 cup fruit juice; stir well.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in fruit and pecans.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: diabetic spice cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine first 8 ingredients.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, egg and salt.

Shape firmly into loaf and place in baking pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Spoon off fat, saving 3 tablespoons drippings. Separate the crescent rolls and place crosswise over top and down sides of meat loaf, overlapping slightly.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla together and add potato chips and pecans.
Stir in the flour.
Form into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of a glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.

title: snicker cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to the instructions on the package. Bake half of the mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350° (325° for glass pan).

title: old-fashioned chocolate gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients into medium mixing bowl.
Preheat greased skillet on medium-high.
Pour mixture into skillet.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and place into glass bowl.
Enjoy with homemade biscuits.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Put 1/2 cup water in blender.
Place gelatin carefully on top of water away from sides of blender.
Add 1/2 cup scalded milk and blend on "high" for 40 seconds.
Add chocolate chips and blend 30 seconds.
Add sugar and vanilla; blend 30 seconds.
Add milk covered ice and blend until dissolved.
While the blender is on, add egg yolks and whipping cream.
Blend another 10 seconds.
Pour into mold or serving dishes and refrigerate until set.

title: bread dough(eatable)
directions: Thaw frozen dough in refrigerator overnight.
Shape dough into small balls.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet. Crack egg and separate out egg white.
Beat white with 1 teaspoon of water in a small bowl.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prepare the pastry in
a
9-inch
deep pie plate.
Cook the bacon and onion in a skillet until the onion is tender and the bacon is done.
Drain the bacon and cut into small pieces. Sprinkle the bacon and the	onion
into the pastry shell.
Top with the green chilies
and
cheese.
Combine the beaten eggs, flour, red pepper, salt and
half
and
half.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.	Bake at 375°
for 40 minutes or until set. Enjoy!

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix well and store in a covered container.
Stir 2 spoonfuls of this Friendship Tea mix into a mug of hot water.
Share with a friend and enjoy.

title: very crisp oven fried chicken
directions: Put oil and butter in jelly roll pan.
Mix the dry ingredients.
Roll chicken pieces in oil, then coat with flour mixture.
Place coated chicken on wax paper; cover with another sheet of wax paper.
Let this sit an hour.
(The flour drying makes the chicken crisp.)
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Turn and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: barbecue pork roast
directions: Make sauce with listed ingredients.
Cook roast in the sauce until it falls off the bone (several hours or overnight in a slow cooker).
Shred meat when done.
Mix well in sauce.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Remove fat next morning.
This is fine fare for quick meals during the holidays.
Makes at least 10 sandwiches.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples.
Combine in blender with 2 cups water, sweetener and spices.
Blend until smooth.
Cook over low heat until thickened, about 45 minutes.
In blender, sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup water and add to boiling apples and puree. Store in refrigerator.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water about 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and cool slightly.
Peel and cut potatoes into 3/4-inch cubes.
Remove yolks from eggs and mash; set whites aside.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Chop egg whites; add bacon, potatoes, onion, celery and Italian dressing.
Fold in mayonnaise mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours. Serves 12.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients. Ginger ale may be added, if desired.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: zesty, spicy brisket
directions: In Dutch oven, sear each side of brisket.
Add 1/2 diced onion,
pepper,
paprika, oregano and salt.
Drain potatoes and add to pot, marinara sauce, water and bay leaves.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Refrigerate
overnight,
then
slice
meat
when
cold. Reheat slices and potatoes in sauce and serve.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Follow the directions on the cake box except reduce the water to 1/2 cup and add canned pumpkin and spice.
Spread into pan and bake as directed on box.
Cool.
Mix cinnamon with frosting and spread on cake.
Decorate with candy.

title: apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in stainless steel or granite roaster. Bake in oven for 4 or 5 hours.
Stir often.
When done, put into hot jars and seal.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine cherry juice, tapioca, sugar and salt; pour over cherries in pastry-lined plate.
Dot with Fluffo.
Cover with slashed top crust.
Flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: poor man's lobster 2
directions: Boil fish in 2 quarts of water with sugar and salt. When fish floats to the top, take out right away. Serve with melted butter or garlic butter.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, salt, ginger and molasses with a little flour. Add the soda dissolved in water and the rest of the flour, then work all together.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut with a plain cutter.
Bake on greased pans about 1-inch apart in an oven at a temperature of 375°.

title: coleslaw
directions: In a large dish mix shredded cabbage, carrots and green onions.
Add vinegar and Equal.
Fold in well.
Add mayonnaise and apple.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Melt margarine and cool slightly.
Add sugar and beaten egg. Combine the yeast and warm water; add to margarine and sugar mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Place in an airtight container. No need to let rise.

title: mushroom creole salad
directions: In a large bowl, lined with lettuce, arrange mushrooms, tomatoes, turkey, zucchini, green pepper and scallion. Toss with salad dressing. Yields 6 to 8 portions.
